ia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Ffrench-pilot-sentenced-for-accidental-killing-of-skydiver%2Famp_articleshow%2F105481281.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Ffrench-pilot-sentenced-for-accidental-killing-of-skydiver%2Famp_articleshow%2F105481281.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20Did%20the%20Union%20Govt's%20Food%20Policy%20Help%3F%20India%E2%80%99s%20Anaemic%2C%20or%20Vitamin%20Businesses%20and%20Big%20NGOs%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24212038%2FIMG_2670.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20third%20and%20final%20story%20in%20the%20series%20on%20the%20policy%20of%20rice%20fortification%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20public-sector%20food%20programme%2C%20examines%20the%20lack%20of%20evidence%20and%20scientific%20consensus%20when%20India%20adopted%20compulsory%20food%20fortification.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20it%20does%20not%20really%20help%20those%20with%20anaemia%20and%20malnutrition%2C%20then%20who%20benefits%3F%20The%20story%20traces%20the%20lobbying%20for%20the%20policy%20by%20a%20handful%20of%20organisations%2C%20substantively%20funded%20by%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20and%20its%20entities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20government%20cut%20budgets%20to%20social%20schemes%20providing%20freshly%20cooked%20and%20local%20food%20drastically.%20Instead%20of%20addressing%20the%20structural%20causes%20of%20hunger%20and%20food%20insecurity%20in%20inequalities%20in%20power%2C%20this%20%E2%80%9Csolution%E2%80%9D%20of%20mandatory%20fortification%2C%20thus%20took%20India%20further%20away%20from%20improving%20food%20diversity%20and%20from%20climate%20resilience.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20parts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fplastic-rice-why-union-govts-experiment-with-an-artificial-grain-is-hard-to-swallow-for-rural-adivasis%5C%22%3Eone%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ffortified-rice-kernel-experiment-testing%5C%22%3Etwo%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EGumla%20(Jharkhand)%2FNew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20a%20breezy%20summer%20morning%20in%20Gumla%2C%20100%20km%20from%20Jharkhand%E2%80%99s%20state%20capital%20Ranchi.%20A%20private%20operator%E2%80%99s%20bus%20departed%20from%20the%20Gumla%20bus%20station%20for%20its%20destination%20in%20remote%20forest%20villages%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epaat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20highlands%20of%20the%20Chhotanagpur%20plateau%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20east%2C%20home%20primarily%20to%20Adivasis.%20Dressed%20in%20clothes%20apt%20for%20a%20business%20meeting%2C%20a%20light%20blue%20shirt%20and%20dark%20trousers%2C%20with%20his%20thick%20mop%20of%20hair%20combed%20neatly%2C%20Rajesh%20Singh%20hopped%20on%20the%20bus.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20quack%20with%20the%20years%20of%20experience%20of%20selling%20dodgy%20medicines%20and%20cures%20in%20this%20Adivasi%20belt%2C%20Singh%20stood%20at%20the%20front%20of%20the%20crowded%20bus.%20He%20began%20advertising%20to%20a%20largely%20disinterested%20but%20wholly%20captive%20audience.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20new%20product!%20Called%20CMD%20%E2%80%93%20Concentrated%20Mineral%20Drops!%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDawa%20dekhna%20ka%20paisa%20nahi%20lagta%20hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E!%20I%20will%20not%20charge%20you%20for%20inspecting%20the%20medicines%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20began%2C%20as%20he%20fished%20out%20a%20packet%20of%2012%20multi-vitamins%20tablets.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20USA%2C%20there%20is%20a%20place%20called%20Utah%E2%80%A6From%20the%20Utah%20lake%2C%20famous%20for%20its%20nutrients%2C%20made%20from%20its%20special%20minerals%2C%20we%20bring%20you%20CMD!%20It%20will%20solve%20all%20your%20problems.%20From%20tooth%20decay%2C%20to%20balding%2C%20from%20addictions%20to%20sugar%20and%20liver%20ailments!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20young%20woman%20farmer%20transporting%20a%20ceramic%20seat%20for%20her%20newly%20built%20toilet%20back%20in%20the%20village%20and%20young%20Adivasi%20men%20returning%20from%20working%20as%20temporary%20migrants%20in%20other%20states%20looked%20on%20as%20Singh%20continued%20the%20staccato%20pitch%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20bring%20it%20you%20from%20the%20USA!%20Just%20for%20Rs%20600!%E2%80%9D%20The%20slick%20salesman%20cited%20a%20sum%20nearly%20thrice%20the%20daily%20wage%20in%20these%20rural%20parts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFinally%2C%20he%20walked%20to%20one%20of%20the%20Adivasi%20men%2C%20Sylvanus%20Ekka%20of%20Jokipokhar%20village%20on%20top%20of%20the%20plateau%2C%20who%20was%20returning%20after%20working%20on%20pineapple%20plantations%20in%20far-off%20coastal%20Kerala.%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBol%20beta%2C%20yehi%20mauqa%20hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Take%20it%20son%2C%20it%20is%20your%20only%20chance!%E2%80%9D%20he%20goaded%20Ekka%20till%20the%20quiet%20man%20carrying%20back%20the%20wages%20of%20last%20few%20months%20agreed%20to%20buy%20one%20packet%20of%20multi-vitamins%20pills%20from%20him.%20Despite%20his%20dodgy%20pseudo-scientific%20claims%2C%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20sale%20was%20successful%20and%20complete.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFar%20from%20Gumla%2C%20nearly%201%2C300%20km%20away%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20organisations%20mainly%20funded%20and%20led%20by%20the%20Bill%20and%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation%20(BMGF)%20and%20international%20aid%20agencies%20have%20in%20a%20similar%20exaggerated%20vein%20pushed%20%E2%80%9Cfood%20fortification%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20factory-made%20vitamins%20and%20minerals%20to%20food%20staples%2C%20as%20a%20cheap%20solution%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20government%20to%20fix%20its%20malnutrition%20and%20anaemia%20problem.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CLarge%20scale%20food%20fortification%E2%80%9D%20is%20the%20addition%20of%20industry-made%20nutrients%20to%20foods%20to%20improve%20their%20nutritional%20quality.%20Advocates%20of%20the%20policy%20argue%20that%20it%20is%20cost%20effective%2C%20and%20does%20not%20require%20changes%20in%20eating%20habits.%20Rice%20is%20a%20staple%20food%20of%20more%20than%20half%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20and%20is%20seen%20as%20suitable%20for%20adopting%20as%20a%20food%20vehicle%20for%20fortification.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24141214%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-2.11.02.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24141214%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-2.11.02.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24141214%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-2.11.02-300x223.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24141214%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-2.11.02-1024x761.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686200%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22892%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMore%20than%20half%20of%20India%20eats%20rice%20as%20a%20staple%20crop%2C%20including%20most%20of%20Adivasi%20smallholder%20farmers%20in%20Jharkhand.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20critics%20of%20this%20policy%2C%20which%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20being%20expanded%20and%20scaled%20up%20nationally%2C%20call%20it%20out%20as%20ineffective%2C%20wasteful%20and%20coercive.%20There%20is%20no%20evidence%2C%20they%20say%2C%20that%20it%20reduces%20anaemia.%20According%20to%20them%2C%20making%20this%20a%20mandatory%20policy%20%E2%80%93%20and%20scaling%20it%20up%20without%20adequate%20infrastructure%20and%20quality%20control%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fplastic-rice-why-union-govts-experiment-with-an-artificial-grain-is-hard-to-swallow-for-rural-adivasis%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esee%20part%20one%20of%20this%20series%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20%E2%80%93%20has%20concerning%20implications%20for%20the%20health%20and%20safety%20of%20vulnerable%20populations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20high%20growth%2C%20India%20has%20some%20of%20the%20highest%20rates%20of%20anaemia%20and%20child%20undernutrition%20globally.%20Within%20South%20Asia%2C%20it%20fares%20worse%20than%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.worldbank.org%2Fendpovertyinsouthasia%2Ftackling-malnutrition-south-asia-8-years%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAfghanistan%2520has%2520the%2520highest%2520rate%2Cregion%2520with%2520rising%2520income%2520levels.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emost%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20countries%2C%20other%20than%20war-torn%20Afghanistan.%20The%20government%20has%20cited%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eseverity%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20health%20problem%20of%20anaemia%20and%20its%20stubborn%20persistence%20%E2%80%93%2058%25%20children%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1795421%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eanaemic%20in%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%202015-%E2%80%9916%20which%20worsened%20to%2067%25%20in%202019-%E2%80%9920%20%E2%80%93%20to%20argue%20for%20food%20fortification.%20On%20one%20hand%2C%20it%20has%20now%20stated%20it%20will%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Ffit%2Fcitizen-fit%2Fanaemia-nfhs-6-questions-dropped-a-mistake%23read-more%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eno%20longer%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20collect%20data%20at%20district%20level%20on%20anaemia%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fexperts-oppose-lowering-who-anaemia-standards-to-local-parameters%2Farticleshow%2F101114181.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esame%20way%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20had%20shown%20it%20getting%20worse.%20On%20the%20other%2C%20it%20has%20succumbed%20to%20a%20silver%20bullet%20%E2%80%9Csolution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr%20Arun%20Gupta%2C%20a%20paediatrician%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20former%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Council%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20Nutrition%20Challenges%2C%20asked%3A%20%E2%80%9CA%20central%20question%20is%2C%20how%20many%20of%20our%20children%20are%20eating%20well%3F%20Why%20is%20the%20other%20rich%20half%20of%20India%20doing%20fine%3F%E2%80%9D%20He%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CData%20show%20that%20below%20two%20years%20of%20age%2C%20only%2010-11%20percent%20infants%20get%20to%20eat%20diverse%20diets%20of%20at%20least%20four%20food%20groups.%20They%20are%20inadequately%20breastfed.%20In%20later%20life%2C%20these%20disadvantages%20becomes%20permanent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr%20Gupta%20said%20that%20so%20few%20children%20in%20the%20country%20get%20to%20eat%20well%20is%20an%20indictment%20of%20the%20state%20and%20of%20society.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24155327%2F2-A-Malnutrition-treatment-center-in-Latehar-JH.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24155327%2F2-A-Malnutrition-treatment-center-in-Latehar-JH.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24155327%2F2-A-Malnutrition-treatment-center-in-Latehar-JH-300x225.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686219%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20dilapidated%20%E2%80%9CTreatment%20Centre%E2%80%9D%20for%20children%20suffering%20from%20malnutrition%20in%20Mahuadanr%20block%20of%20Jharkhand.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CInstead%20of%20addressing%20the%20causes%20of%20poor%20diets%2C%20it%20has%20led%20India%E2%80%99s%20government%20to%20believe%20that%20they%20must%20come%20out%20with%20something%20to%20show.%20That%20has%20become%20an%20opportunity%20for%20the%20corporations%2C%20which%20have%20been%20advancing%20and%20propagating%20the%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%9Chidden%20hunger%E2%80%9D%20concept%20since%20a%20few%20years%2C%20to%20sell%20micronutrients%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Dr%20Gupta.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHow%20rice%20is%20being%20fortified%20is%20a%20dried%20powder%20%E2%80%9Cpre-mix%E2%80%9D%20of%20vitamins%20and%20minerals%20%E2%80%93%20iron%2C%20vitamin%20B12%2C%20folic%20acid%20%E2%80%93%20is%20added%20to%20powdered%20rice.%20The%20paste%20is%20passed%20through%20pasta-extrusion%20equipment%20to%20manufacture%20new%20grains%2C%20with%20a%20slightly%20artificial%20appearance%20compared%20to%20natural%20rice.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%20budgeted%20an%20estimated%20Rs%202%2C900%20crore%20a%20year%20for%20implementing%20rice%20fortification%20all%20over%20India.%20Initially%2C%20in%20Phase%201%20in%20112%20%E2%80%9Caspirational%E2%80%9D%20or%20poor%20districts%2C%20it%20provided%20Rs%20722.7%20crore%3B%20in%20phase%202%20in%20250%20districts%20with%20high%20malnourishment%20the%20budget%20was%20Rs%201445.4%20crore%3B%20and%20phase%203%20in%20all%20India%20had%20a%20budget%20of%20Rs%202%2C810%20crore.%20The%20three%20phases%E2%80%99%20combined%20budget%20amounts%20to%20Rs%204%2C978.1%20crore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPublic%20health%20experts%20and%20right%20to%20food%20activists%20have%20termed%20this%20a%20waste%20of%20public%20resources.%20Activists%20have%20accused%20India%E2%80%99s%20statutory%20food%20safety%20regulator%2C%20the%20Food%20Safety%20and%20Standards%20Authority%20of%20India%20(FSSAI)%2C%20of%20failing%20to%20avoid%20conflicts%20of%20interest%20and%20of%20obfuscating%20information.%20They%20said%20by%20hosting%20a%20lobbying%20body%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20whose%20members%20were%20funded%20by%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20%E2%80%93%20for%20over%20three%20years%20inside%20its%20offices%2C%20the%20FSSAI%20allowed%20nutraceutical%20and%20food%20corporations%20to%20influence%20decision-making%2C%20funding%2C%20implementation%20and%20evaluations%20to%20fortify%20food%20staples%20mandatorily%20in%20public%20schemes.%20This%20opened%20up%20a%20new%20market%20for%20multinational%20vitamin%20companies%20and%20the%20large%20food%20industry%2C%20while%20doing%20little%20to%20address%20the%20crises%20of%20chronic%20under-nourishment%20and%20anaemia%20among%20India%E2%80%99s%20poor.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20fortified%20food%2C%20supplied%20as%20a%20compulsory%20measure%20in%20grains%20supplied%20monthly%20as%20food%20rations%20and%20in%20children%E2%80%99s%20meals%2C%20is%20not%20accepted%20in%20rural%20communities.%20But%20they%20have%20little%20choice%20to%20forgo%20the%20food%20subsidies%20they%20survive%20on.%20It%20further%20diverts%20attention%20away%20from%20more%20sustainable%20approaches%20rooted%20in%20local%2C%20fresh%20and%20diversified%20food%2C%20they%20contended.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24155512%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-3.54.42.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24155512%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-3.54.42.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24155512%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-3.54.42-300x165.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24155512%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-3.54.42-1024x563.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22660%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20variety%20of%20small%20fish%20and%20vegetables%20sold%20at%20a%20weekly%20haat%20or%20the%20village%20market%20in%20Latehar%2C%20Jharkhand.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EOpaque%20policy-lobbying%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20first%20mentioned%20the%20food%20fortification%20policy%20in%20a%20radio%20programme%20on%20August%2025%2C%202019.%20Most%20Indian%20residents%20first%20heard%20about%20it%20when%20the%20prime%20minister%20announced%20it%20in%20his%20Independence%20Day%20speech%20in%20August%202021.%20But%20the%20groundwork%20for%20the%20new%20scheme%20was%20laid%20much%20earlier%2C%20shows%20information%20obtained%20through%20interviews%2C%20and%20from%20Right%20to%20Information%20applications%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20public%20documents%20first%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F13ma1qijGsp0OUIMNetJgHRcYtHzjTs0W%2Fview%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epublished%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Reporters%20Collective.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20December%2010%2C%202015%2C%20Bill%20Gates%2C%20the%20co-chair%20of%20the%20Bill%20and%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20and%20Ratan%20Tata%2C%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20board%20of%20Tata%20Trusts%20co-authored%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fblogs%2Ftoi-editorials%2Fnew-nutrition-report-underscores-the-importance-of-leadership-in-addressing-stunting-in-india%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eop-ed%20article%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20In%20it%2C%20they%20advocated%20focusing%20on%201%2C000%20days%20between%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20pregnancy%20and%20her%20child%E2%80%99s%20second%20birthday%20and%20artificially%20adding%20micronutrients%20to%20food%20as%20among%20the%20top%20solutions%20for%20Indians%20suffering%20from%20malnutrition.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20these%20approaches%20were%20earlier%20critiqued%20as%20inadequate%20by%20the%20UN%20former%20Special%20Rapporteur%20Olivier%20De%20Schutter%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2FDocuments%2FHRBodies%2FHRCouncil%2FRegularSession%2FSession19%2FA-HRC-19-59_en.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehis%20report%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20right%20to%20food%20on%20December%2026%2C%202011.%20Schutter%20warned%20that%20inequitable%20access%20to%20food%20is%20the%20structural%20cause%20of%20malnutrition%2C%20which%20cannot%20be%20addressed%20by%20the%20focus%20on%20merely%20%E2%80%9C1%2C000%20days%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20still%20leaves%20out%20children%2C%20teenagers%2C%20older%20people%20and%20women%20who%20are%20not%20pregnant.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstead%2C%20he%20emphasised%20the%20need%20for%20food%20systems%20inclusive%20of%20the%20poorest%20and%20small-scale%20farmers%2C%20that%20move%20away%20from%20mono-cropping%20staples%20such%20as%20only%20rice%20to%20diverse%20farming%20systems%2C%20protecting%20lactating%20women%20from%20economic%20pressures%20to%20support%20breastfeeding%2C%20and%20improving%20women%E2%80%99s%20direct%20access%20to%20productive%20resources.%20He%20noted%20fortified%20foods%20may%20be%20necessary%20only%20%E2%80%9Cwhere%20local%20production%20is%20insufficiently%20diversified%20and%20incapable%20of%20supplying%20full%20range%20of%20foods%20for%20adequate%20diets%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20is%20not%20the%20case%20in%20a%20vast%20agrarian%20country%20such%20as%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20both%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20and%20Tata%20Trusts%20systematically%20advocated%20to%20fortify%20staple%20food%20with%20added%20micronutrients%20occupying%20an%20influential%20position%20in%20FSSAI%2C%20inside%20the%20Government%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%2021%2C%202016%2C%20the%20FSSAI%20set%20up%20a%20%E2%80%9CFood%20Fortification%20Resource%20Center%E2%80%9D%20(FFRC)%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20Bill%20Gates%2C%20the%20co-chair%20of%20BMGF%2C%20along%20with%20senior%20staff%20of%20the%20Tata%20Trusts%20at%20its%20New%20Delhi%20office.%20The%20FSSAI%20is%20a%20central%20body%20whose%20role%20is%20to%20regulate%20the%20manufacture%2C%20processing%2C%20distribution%2C%20sale%20and%20import%20of%20food%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20531px)%2085vw%2C%20531px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160107%2F4-Pawan-Agarwal-accompanying-Gates.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22531%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160107%2F4-Pawan-Agarwal-accompanying-Gates.png%20531w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160107%2F4-Pawan-Agarwal-accompanying-Gates-300x170.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686224%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFormer%20FSSAI%20chairperson%20Pawan%20Agarwal%20accompanying%20Bill%20Gates%20at%20the%20FSSAI%20building%20for%20the%20launch%20of%20FFRC%20portal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160151%2F5-bill-gates-at-launch-of-FFRC-website.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160151%2F5-bill-gates-at-launch-of-FFRC-website.jpeg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160151%2F5-bill-gates-at-launch-of-FFRC-website-300x200.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686226%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22531%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBill%20Gates%2C%20co-chair%20of%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20at%20the%20launch%20of%20FFRC%20portal%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20primary%20entity%20of%20the%20FFRC%20was%20the%20Tata%20Trusts%2C%20the%20philanthropic%20arm%20of%20the%20Indian%20corporate%20giant%20Tata%20Company%2C%20which%20has%20a%20range%20of%20businesses%2C%20including%20in%20food%20and%20nutraceuticals.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFSSAI%20officials%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20other%20key%20members%20of%20the%20FFRC%20included%20the%20US%20NGO%20PATH%2C%20the%20Canadian%20NGO%20Nutrition%20International%20(NI)%2C%20and%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20World%20Food%20Programme%20(WFP).%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20explained%20in%20the%20following%20section%2C%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20funds%20each%20of%20these%20entities%20to%20promote%20and%20lobby%20for%20large%20scale%20food%20fortification.%20Some%20of%20them%20have%20over%20the%20years%20partnered%20with%20the%20global%20food%20and%20fertiliser%20industry%2C%20as%20well%20as%20mining%20industry%2C%20in%20all%20of%20whose%20interests%20is%20the%20increase%20in%20business%20of%20manufacturing%20synthetic%20micro-nutrients.%20This%20has%20led%20to%20questions%20on%20the%20conflict%20of%20interest%20of%20these%20FFRC%20partner%20NGOs%20and%20their%20associated%20corporate%20entities%20that%20have%20a%20financial%20interest%20in%20fortification.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20a%20major%20component%20of%20the%20food%20fortification%20push%20is%20on%20rice%20with%20iron%20and%20vitamin%20B%2C%20the%20government%20has%20also%20made%20fortification%20compulsory%20in%20other%20food%20staples%20such%20as%20edible%20oil%2C%20milk%20and%20wheat%2C%20with%20other%20micronutrients%20including%20vitamin%20A%20and%20D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20notified%20standards%20and%20norms%20for%20how%20several%20food%20staples%20may%20be%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2Fnewsite%2FPrintRelease.aspx%3Frelid%3D177039%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Evoluntarily%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20fortified%20in%202018.%20But%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nutraingredients-asia.com%2FArticle%2F2019%2F10%2F07%2FFood-fortification-in-India-Supply-and-demand-alignment-the-main-hurdle%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eregulators%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20well%20as%20industry%20bodies%20in%20rural%20areas%20such%20as%20Jharkhand%20stated%20in%20interviews%20that%20the%20demand%20for%20fortified%20food%20in%20markets%20remained%20slow%20to%20take%20off.%20Including%20it%20mandatorily%20in%20rice%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20social%20safety%20net%20programmes%2C%20covering%20more%20than%20813%20million%2C%20led%20to%20one%20of%20biggest%20market%20expansions%20ever%20for%20such%20products.%20It%20has%20never%20been%20tried%20before%20in%20any%20other%20country%20mandatorily%20on%20such%20a%20large%20and%20diverse%20population%20having%20diverse%20food%20systems%2C%20and%20its%20impact%20at%20scale%20remains%20unknown.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20fortification%20scheme%E2%80%99s%202019%20operational%20guidelines%20as%20well%20as%20a%20presentation%20titled%20%E2%80%9CNeed%2C%20Scientific%20Evidence%20and%20Alternatives%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20food%20ministry%20of%20June%2021%2C%202021%20supported%20fortification%20by%20repeating%20that%20rice%20is%20already%20fortified%20mandatorily%20in%20the%20countries%20Costa%20Rica%2C%20Nicaragua%2C%20Panama%2C%20Papua%20New%20Guinea%20and%20the%20Philippines.%20The%20combined%20population%20of%20these%20five%20countries%20is%20nearly%2038%20million%20or%203.8%20crore.%20Thus%2C%20doing%20it%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20public%20distribution%20system%20meant%20making%20it%20mandatory%20food%20for%20a%20population%20nearly%2020%20times%20greater%2C%20in%20one%20fell%20swoop.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160355%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.03.17.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160355%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.03.17.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160355%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.03.17-300x208.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160355%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.03.17-1024x708.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686228%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22830%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWomen%20in%20Jharkhand%20carry%20rice%20grains%20back%20to%20their%20homes.%20India%E2%80%99s%20public%20distribution%20system%20provides%20grains%20at%20nominal%20prices%20or%20for%20free%20to%20the%20poorest%20two-thirds%20of%20population.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECreating%20a%20market%20to%20fix%20malnutrition%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGlobally%2C%20the%20advocacy%20for%20chemically-fortifying%20food%20is%20led%20by%20an%20international%20consortium%20called%20the%20Global%20Alliance%20for%20Improved%20Nutrition%20(GAIN)%2C%20which%20is%20registered%20as%20a%20Swiss%20NGO.%20The%20Gates%20Foundation%20had%20launched%20GAIN%20in%202002%20with%20a%20US%20%24%2050%20million%20grant%20with%20an%20aim%20to%20address%20malnutrition%20by%20offering%20economic%20incentives%20to%20food%20corporations%2C%20such%20as%20Heinz%2C%20Kraft%2C%20and%20vitamin%20manufacturers%20such%20as%20Roche.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReporting%20about%20this%20consortium%E2%80%99s%20launch%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20the%20headline%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2FSB1020886090206568560%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGates%20Fights%20Malnutrition%20With%20Cheese%2C%20Ketchup%20and%20Other%20Fortified%20Food%20Items%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20noted%2C%20in%20exchange%20for%20focusing%20on%20micronutrient%20deficiencies%2C%20GAIN%20offered%20the%20companies%20assistance%20in%20lobbying%20for%20favourable%20tariffs%20and%20tax%20rates%20and%20speedier%20regulatory%20review%20of%20new%20products%20in%20targeted%20countries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGAIN%20has%20worked%20with%20over%20600%20companies%20and%20civil%20society%20organisations%20in%2040%20countries.%20In%202014%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.welthungerhilfe.de%2Ffileadmin%2Fpictures%2Fpublications%2Fen%2Fstudies_analysis%2F2014_study_food_fortification_techno_fix_en.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E70%25%20of%20GAIN%E2%80%99s%20budget%20for%20fortification%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20focused%20on%20in%20India%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Indonesia%20and%20China.%20In%20India%2C%20GAIN%E2%80%99s%20interventions%20focus%20primarily%20on%20working%20with%20private%20sector%20to%20expand%20food%20fortification%20initiatives%20in%20wheat%2C%20edible%20oil%2C%20milk%20and%20salt.%20It%20runs%20a%20%E2%80%9CGAIN%20Premix%20Facility%E2%80%9D%20to%20make%20premix%20sale%20and%20procurement%20easier.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gainhealth.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpublications%2Fdocuments%2Ffinancial-statements-2021-2022.pdf%5C%22%3EUnder%20this%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20certifies%20producers%20of%20pre-mixes%2C%20provides%20guarantees%20for%20payments%20to%20premix%20suppliers%2C%20and%20offers%20extended%20credit%20terms%20to%20customers%20purchasing%20premix%20adding%20it%20to%20food.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.welthungerhilfe.de%2Ffileadmin%2Fpictures%2Fpublications%2Fen%2Fstudies_analysis%2F2014_study_food_fortification_techno_fix_en.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2014%20critique%20of%20the%20consortium%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20points%20out%20that%20GAIN%E2%80%99s%20Business%20Alliance%20for%20Food%20Fortification%20(which%20was%20superseded%20by%20the%20Scaling%20Up%20Nutrition%20%E2%80%93%20SUN%20%E2%80%93%20business%20network%2C%20launched%20in%202014%2C%20of%20which%20GAIN%20and%20the%20World%20Food%20Programme%20are%20co-hosts)%20included%20corporations%20such%20as%20Coca-Cola%2C%20Unilever%2C%20Cargill%2C%20BASF%2C%20many%20of%20which%20have%20been%20accused%20by%20civil%20society%20organisations%20of%20breaches%20of%20human%20rights%20and%20code%20violations%20that%20contribute%20to%20malnutrition.%20SUN%20and%20GAIN%20have%20been%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FDocuments%2FHRBodies%2FHRCouncil%2FRegularSession%2FSession19%2FA-HRC-19-59_en.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecriticised%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20failing%20to%20%E2%80%9Cexplicitly%20align%20their%20initiatives%20with%20human%20rights%2C%20including%20the%20right%20to%20food%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%2C%20critics%20point%20out%20that%20financing%20of%20industrial%20food%20production%20by%20GAIN%20might%20create%20problems%20for%20local%20producers%20that%20lack%20the%20adequate%20technology.%20This%20is%20already%20being%20faced%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20rural%20small%20rice%20mills%2C%20as%20reported%20in%20this%20series%E2%80%99%20previous%20article.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20critics%20of%20its%20philanthro-capitalism%20such%20as%20of%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brot-fuer-die-welt.de%2Ffileadmin%2Fmediapool%2F2_Downloads%2FFachinformationen%2FSonstiges%2Fstudy_philanthropic_power_and_development.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexpress%20the%20concern%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20even%20as%20such%20foundations%20and%20consortium%20gain%20access%20and%20influence%20in%20many%20programme%20areas%2C%20little%20or%20no%20governing%20framework%20or%20oversight%20exists%20to%20show%20how%20they%20operate%2C%20or%20make%20them%20or%20their%20results%20accountable%20to%20public%20mandates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20India%20too%2C%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20through%20a%20mix%20of%20grant-making%2C%20personal%20networking%20and%20advocacy%2C%20placed%20itself%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20hub%20promoting%20fortification%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20public%20sector%20food%20schemes%2C%20selling%20a%20quick-win%20solution%2C%20but%20offering%20little%20transparency%20or%20accountability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160532%2F7-by-IPES-Foods-iceberg-on-lobby.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160532%2F7-by-IPES-Foods-iceberg-on-lobby.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160532%2F7-by-IPES-Foods-iceberg-on-lobby-300x267.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160532%2F7-by-IPES-Foods-iceberg-on-lobby-1024x911.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686229%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221067%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECorporates%E2%80%99%20influence%20on%20food%20systems%20has%20grown.%20We%20need%20participatory%20solutions%20to%20democratise%20food%20decision-making%20in%20public%20interest%2C%20say%20IPES-Food%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAn%20%E2%80%9Cembedded%E2%80%9D%20lobbyists%E2%80%99%20hub%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20stated%20earlier%2C%20an%20FFRC%20was%20set%20up%20inside%20the%20FFSAI%20in%20November%202016%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20Bill%20Gates.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Tata%20Trusts%20magazine%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhorizons.tatatrusts.org%2F2019%2Fseptember%2Ftata-trusts-nutrition-food-fortification.html%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHorizons%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20in%20its%20edition%20of%20September%202019%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20a%20cover%20titled%20%E2%80%9CNutrition%20Now%E2%80%9D%2C%20stated%20that%20Tata%20Trusts%20is%20supporting%20the%20%E2%80%9C10-member%E2%80%9D%20FFRC%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhich%20is%20embedded%20in%20FSSAI%E2%80%9D%20and%20works%20with%20a%20spectrum%20of%20stakeholders%20%E2%80%9Cto%20propagate%20and%20promote%20fortification%E2%80%9D.%20The%20article%20admits%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20most%20difficult%20bit%20is%20ushering%20in%20a%20bigger%20number%20of%20consumers%20into%20the%20fortification%20circle%E2%80%9D%20but%20does%20not%20question%20why%20it%20is%20so.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20magazine%20interviewed%20Shawn%20Baker%20of%20the%20Gates%20Foundation.%20Baker%2C%20who%20was%20the%20first%20director%20of%20nutrition%20at%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20inaugural%20chief%20nutritionist%20at%20USAID%20and%20earlier%20worked%20with%20Gates%20Global%20Fund%20SUN%2C%20told%20the%20magazine%20that%20as%20Tata%20is%20a%20trusted%20name%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccollaborating%20with%20Tata%20Trusts%20is%20one%20of%20our%20make%20or%20break%20partnerships%E2%80%9D%20on%20nutrition%20in%20India.%20In%20the%20same%20interview%2C%20Baker%20mentions%20that%20in%20West%20Africa%2C%20large%20scale%20food%20fortification%20is%20going%20on%20since%202000%20in%2015%20countries%20in%20salt%2C%20cereals%2C%20flour%20and%20cooking%20oil%2C%20though%20the%20%E2%80%9Cabsolute%20number%20of%20stunted%20children%20are%20projected%20to%20increase%E2%80%9D%20after%20%E2%80%9Crapid%20demographic%20growth%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlong%20with%20Tata%20Trusts%2C%20the%20FFRC%20included%20a%20number%20of%20Gates-funded%20international%20NGOs%2C%20such%20as%20PATH.%20It%20had%20no%20other%20local%20civil%20society%20organisations%2C%20who%20did%20not%20have%20links%20to%20food%20corporations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPATH%20is%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.globalpolicy.org%2Fcomponent%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2F270-general%2F52829-philanthropic-power-and-development-who-shapes-the-agenda.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cproduct%20development%20organisation%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20initiated%20by%20Ford%20Foundation%20in%201977%2C%20which%20is%20heavily%20funded%20by%20the%20Bill%20and%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation.%20Both%20share%20longstanding%20institutional%20ties.%20In%201998%2C%20before%20the%20official%20establishment%20of%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20the%20Gates%20created%20the%20Bill%20%26amp%3B%20Melinda%20Gates%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Vaccine%20Programme%20with%20a%20donation%20of%20%24100%20million%20and%20this%20was%20administered%20by%20PATH%E2%80%99s%20secretariat%20in%20Seattle.%20As%20per%20its%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.path.org%2Fabout%2Ffinances%2Ffinancial-documents%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2022%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20financial%20report%2C%2043%25%20of%20its%20funding%20was%20from%20one%20private%20foundation%2C%20and%2032%25%20from%20United%20States%20government%20agencies.%20PATH%E2%80%99s%20proprietary%20technology%20%E2%80%9CUltra%20Rice%E2%80%9D%20is%20being%20used%20in%20the%20fortified%20rice%20being%20given%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENutrition%20International%20(incorporated%20as%20the%20Micronutrient%20Initiative%20in%202001)%20is%20a%20Canadian%20NGO%20that%20works%20to%20eliminate%20vitamin%20and%20mineral%20deficiencies%20in%20poor%20countries.%20In%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkisanswaraj.in%2F2023%2F02%2F16%2Findias-massive-food-fortification-programme-ridden-with-conflict-of-interest-new-report%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edetailed%20report%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Alliance%20for%20Sustainable%20and%20Holistic%20Agriculture(ASHA)%20activists%20pointed%20out%20that%20Nutrition%20International%20It%20was%20a%20founding%20donor%20of%20GAIN.%20It%20has%20some%20private%20partners%20which%20have%20changed%20over%20the%20years.%20Many%20of%20these%20are%20manufacturers%20of%20micronutrients%20that%20they%20export%20to%20the%20countries%20such%20as%20India%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20food%20and%20chemicals%20companies%20such%20as%20Mott%20MacDonald%2C%20Royal%20DSM%2C%20BASF%2C%20and%20as%20well%20as%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20largest%20diversified%20mining%20company%2C%20Teck%20Resources%20Limited%2C%20which%20manufactures%20zinc.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20stated%20earlier%2C%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20funded%20each%20of%20these%20entities%20to%20promote%20and%20lobby%20for%20large%20scale%20food%20fortification%20in%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gatesfoundation.org%2Fabout%2Fcommitted-grants%2F2021%2F10%2Finv036698%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20instance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20BMGF%20gave%20the%20Jamshetji%20Tata%20Trust%20%241%20million%20for%20%E2%80%9Cnutrition%20advocacy%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20as%20its%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20intermediary%20for%20smallholder%20farmer%20investment%E2%80%9D%20(2015-%E2%80%9911)%2C%20and%20Sir%20Dorabji%20Tata%20Trusts%20%243%20million%20for%20%E2%80%9CFood%20Fortification%20MIYCN(maternal%20and%20child%20nutrition)%20Joint%20Programming%20Platform%E2%80%9D%20in%202016.%20It%20gave%20PATH%20a%20grant%20of%20%244.85%20million%20to%20%E2%80%9Cscale%20up%20rice%20fortification%20in%20India%E2%80%9D.%20In%202020%2C%20it%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gatesfoundation.org%2Fabout%2Fcommitted-grants%2F2020%2F11%2Finv006014%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egave%20Nutrition%20International%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%241.5%20million%20to%20scale%20up%20large%20scale%20food%20fortification%20using%20rice%2C%20oil%2C%20double%20fortified%20salt%20through%20the%20social%20safety%20net%20programmes.%20Recently%2C%20in%20October%202023%2C%20it%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gatesfoundation.org%2Fabout%2Fcommitted-grants%2F2023%2F10%2Finv-056316%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egave%20it%20%242%20million%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20promote%20double%20fortified%20salt%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160652%2F8-FFRC-partners-as-per-earlier-FSSAI-website.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22602%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160652%2F8-FFRC-partners-as-per-earlier-FSSAI-website.png%20602w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160652%2F8-FFRC-partners-as-per-earlier-FSSAI-website-300x232.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686231%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22465%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPartners%20of%20the%20FFRC%2C%20as%20per%20an%20earlier%20page%20on%20FSSAI%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20for%20the%20fourth%20member%20of%20the%20FFRC%2C%20the%20World%20Food%20Programme%20(WFP)%2C%20the%20head%20of%20WFP%20is%20appointed%20by%20the%20US%20government%20and%20it%20receives%20most%20of%20its%20current%20funding%20from%20US%20government.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wfp.org%2Fpartners%2Fprivate-sector%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20lists%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20as%20the%20first%20among%20its%20donors%20among%20foundations%20from%20across%20the%20world%2C%20and%20the%20corporation%20DSM%20as%20a%20partner%20on%20fortification.%20This%20feature%20of%20earmarked%20funds%20from%20private%20donors%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.globalpolicy.org%2Fcomponent%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2F270-general%2F52829-philanthropic-power-and-development-who-shapes-the-agenda.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecriticised%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20contributing%20to%20institutional%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.2030spotlight.org%2Fen%2Fbook%2F1883%2Fchapter%2Fsdg-3-philanthrocapitalism-global-health-and-nutrition-analysis-and-implications%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eweakening%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20and%20its%20specialised%20agencies%2C%20while%20also%20undermining%20implementation%20of%20integrated%20development%20strategies%20at%20national%20level.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20agencies%20were%20assigned%20as%20partners%20of%20state%20governments%20to%20implement%20the%20policy%20in%20states.%20For%20example%2C%20PATH%20was%20made%20a%20development%20partner%20by%20FFRC%20for%20Jharkhand%20and%20several%20North%20Eastern%20states%2C%20Nutrition%20International%20was%20appointed%20for%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20FSSAI%20denied%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99s%20RTI%20requests%20sharing%20any%20contract%20agreements%2C%20or%20Memorandum%20of%20Understanding%20(MoUs)%20with%20the%20terms%20and%20conditions%20signed%20with%20these%20%E2%80%9Cdevelopment%20partners%E2%80%9D%2C%20including%20the%20Tata%20Trusts.%20On%20their%20part%2C%20none%20of%20these%20organisations%20responded%20to%20email%20requests%20for%20commenting%20on%2C%20or%20sharing%20the%20terms%20of%20agreement%20for%20the%20work%20done%20as%20part%20of%20the%20FFRC%20in%20the%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160758%2F9-RTI-rejected.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22837%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160758%2F9-RTI-rejected.png%20837w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160758%2F9-RTI-rejected-300x158.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686233%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22442%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFSSAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20RTI%20requests%20on%20sharing%20any%20MOU%20or%20written%20agreement%20with%20any%20of%20FFRC%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20organisations%20do%20not%20make%20a%20secret%20of%20their%20funds%20and%20lobbying%20to%20push%20for%20this%20policy.%20Some%20of%20them%20took%20credit%20for%20it%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Ftatatrusts%2Fstatus%2F1310918912586870786%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esocial%20media%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20in%20public%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.path.org%2Fprograms%2Fprimary-health-care%2Ffood-fortification%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estatements%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20But%20in%20response%20to%20emailed%20questionnaires%2C%20they%20took%20no%20accountability%20or%20questions%20on%20its%20impact%20when%20the%20infrastructure%20of%20quality%20control%2C%20including%20laboratory%20infrastructure%20to%20test%20for%20micronutrients%2C%20were%20absent%20in%20India.%20They%20also%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20question%20on%20the%20risks%20of%20feeding%20iron-fortified%20rice%20as%20a%20mandatory%20measure%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fplastic-rice-why-union-govts-experiment-with-an-artificial-grain-is-hard-to-swallow-for-rural-adivasis%5C%22%3Ethere%20is%20a%20health%20advisory%20against%20giving%20this%20to%20thousands%20living%20with%20thalassemia%2C%20sickle%20cell%20anaemia%2C%20or%20malaria%2C%20TB%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0to%20whom%20increased%20iron%20intake%20can%20cause%20harm.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%202017%20onwards%2C%20central%20government%20meetings%20to%20decide%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20food%20fortification%20policy%20between%20various%20ministries%2C%20the%20FSSAI%20and%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20planning%20body%2C%20RTI%20documents%20show%2C%20were%20attended%20by%20senior%20staff%20of%20Tata%20Trusts%2C%20GAIN%2C%20and%20PATH.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20revolving%20door%20existed%20between%20these%20organisations.%20For%20example%2C%20RTI%20documents%20show%2C%20PATH%E2%80%99s%20Project%20Lead%20of%20Nutrition%2C%20Rohini%20Saran%2C%20attended%20government%20meetings%20on%20fortification%20hired%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20a%20dep%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Euty%20lead%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eof%20the%20FFRC%20inside%20the%20FSSAI.%20India%E2%80%99s%20central%20food%20safety%20regulator%2C%20the%20FSSAI%2C%20during%20a%20large%20this%20period%20was%20led%20by%20the%20government%20official%20Pawan%20Agarwal%2C%20who%20was%20the%20FSSAI%20chairperson%20from%20December%202015%20till%20February%202020.%20A%20year%20after%20his%20retirement%2C%20Agarwal%20started%20working%20for%20PATH%20in%202022%20to%20work%20as%20a%20consultant%20on%20food%20fortification%2C%20shows%20Agarwal%E2%80%99s%20LinkedIn%20profile.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20advised%20PATH%20on%20rice%20fortification%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Agarwal%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20at%20his%20newly-founded%20NGO%20the%20Food%20Future%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%20office%20in%20central%20Delhi.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20I%20am%20no%20longer%20working%20PATH%2C%20though%20my%20social%20media%20still%20mentions%20it%20as%20ongoing%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20being%20asked%20about%20the%20agreements%20or%20MOUs%20signed%20by%20the%20FSSAI%20to%20host%20a%20hub%20to%20work%20with%20these%20development%20partners%20funded%20by%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20Agarwal%20clarified%20that%20there%20were%20no%20written%20agreements%2C%20or%20concrete%20terms%20and%20conditions.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20an%20informal%20arrangement%20to%20work%20together%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CAt%20the%20time%2C%20our%20focus%20was%20that%20when%20the%20decision%20(to%20fortify%20food)%20has%20been%20taken%20then%20we%20should%20do%20it%20right.%20That%20is%20why%20the%20hub%20FFRC%20was%20set%20up.%20Later%2C%20in%20my%20tenure%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20take%20up%20digitisation%20of%20the%20whole%20(fortification)%20system%2C%20audits%20for%20ensuring%20quality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161103%2F10-screenshot-of-GAIN-Ed-launching-NGO.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22783%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161103%2F10-screenshot-of-GAIN-Ed-launching-NGO.png%20783w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161103%2F10-screenshot-of-GAIN-Ed-launching-NGO-300x206.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686234%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22538%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELawrence%20Haddad%2C%20who%20is%20GAIN%E2%80%99s%20executive%20director%20since%202016%2C%20at%20the%20launch%20of%20former%20FSSAI%20chairperson%20Pawan%20Agarwal%E2%80%99s%20NGO%20in%20Delhi%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EActivists%20warn%20that%20though%20the%20government%20and%20these%20partners%20formally%20states%20it%20is%20just%20one%20approach%20%E2%80%9Ccorporate-led%20fortification%20is%20on%20its%20way%20to%20becoming%20the%20main%20policy%20thrust%E2%80%9D.%20Currently%2C%20holistic%20balanced%20natural%20diets%2C%20produced%2C%20processed%20by%20communities%20themselves%2C%20do%20not%20get%20the%20same%20support.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20criticism%20is%20supported%20by%20comparing%20the%20budgets%20for%20fortification%20and%20millets.%20The%20union%20government%20is%20heavily%20advertising%20that%20growing%20millets%20will%20allow%20Indians%20to%20access%20better%20nutrition%20than%20rice%20and%20build%20climate%20resilience%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20farms.%20But%20for%20five%20years%2C%20from%202018%20till%202023%2C%20it%20gave%20a%20budget%20for%20%E2%80%9Cnutri-cereals%E2%80%9D%20mission%2C%20on%20millets%20of%20only%20Rs%201031.4%20crore.%20The%20budget%20provided%20for%20supplying%20chemically%20fortifying%20rice%20in%20one%20year%20is%20nearly%20three%20times%2C%20at%20Rs%202%2C900%20crore.%20%E2%80%9CIts%20lack%20of%20serious%20attention%20to%20millets%20or%20local%20foods%20is%20also%20evident%20if%20one%20compares%20the%20mission%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1776581%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520total%2520approved%2520cost%2520of%2Cvarious%2520state%2520annual%2520action%2520plans%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eoil%20palm%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20budget%2C%20an%20agricultural%20commodity%20with%20little%20nutritional%20use%2C%20which%20was%20even%20larger%20at%20Rs%2011%2C000%20crore%20for%203-4%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20pointed%20out%20a%20senior%20official%20of%20Odisha%E2%80%99s%20Millet%20Mission%2C%20who%20requested%20to%20not%20be%20named.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161204%2F11-my-RTI-on-millets-budget.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161204%2F11-my-RTI-on-millets-budget.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161204%2F11-my-RTI-on-millets-budget-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161204%2F11-my-RTI-on-millets-budget-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686235%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAs%20per%20response%20to%20The%20Wire%E2%80%99s%20RTI%20request%20the%20budgets%20for%20growing%20millets%20is%20far%20less%20than%20that%20allocated%20for%20fortifying%20rice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EQuestions%20were%20also%20raised%20early%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20largest%20food%20product%20marketing%20organisation.%20The%20apex%20organisation%20of%20the%20dairy%20cooperatives%2C%20Gujarat%20Cooperative%20Milk%20Federation%20Limited%E2%80%99s%20then%20managing%20director%20RS%20Sodhi%20on%20October%203%2C%202019%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20NITI%20Aayog%20expressing%20Amul%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Creservations%20against%20jumping%20on%20the%20bandwagon%20of%20mass%20synthetic%20vitamin%20fortification%E2%80%9D%20of%20food%20staples.%20He%20instead%20advocated%20for%20only%20targeted%20fortification%20administered%20to%20only%20the%20persons%20who%20really%20needed%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAgarwal%20added%20that%20though%20he%20found%20value%20in%20fortification%20of%20milk%20and%20edible%20oil%2C%20he%20had%20found%20rice%20fortification%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20complex%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20difficult%20to%20ensure%20as%20being%20effective.%20%E2%80%9CI%20now%20see%20human%20nutrition%20is%20far%20more%20complex%2C%20than%20a%20cookie-cutter%20solution%20such%20as%20this%20would%20be%20able%20to%20solve%20for.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161251%2F12-Amul-opposed-mandatory-vitamin-fortification.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22797%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161251%2F12-Amul-opposed-mandatory-vitamin-fortification.png%20797w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161251%2F12-Amul-opposed-mandatory-vitamin-fortification-300x139.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686236%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22370%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERS%20Sodhi%2C%20then%20its%20managing%20director%2C%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20NITI%20Ayog%20expressing%20Amul%E2%80%99s%20discomfort%20with%20%E2%80%9Cjumping%20on%20the%20bandwagon%20of%20mass%20synthetic%20vitamin%20fortification%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3ELack%20of%20scientific%20consensus%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20notified%20target%20concentrations%20for%20fortification%20of%20different%20nutrients%20in%20several%20food%20staples%20in%202018.%20This%20was%20based%20on%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20FSSAI%E2%80%99s%20scientific%20panels.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20the%20choice%20to%20fortify%20or%20not%20was%20voluntary.%20But%20in%202020%2C%20it%20was%20made%20mandatory%20for%20some%20micronutrients.%20Supplying%20fortified%20rice%20mandatorily%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20public-sector%20food%20programmes%2C%20which%20the%20poor%20rely%20on%2C%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nutraingredients-asia.com%2FArticle%2F2018%2F12%2F19%2FMandatory-rice-fortification-for-public-programmes-in-India-by-December-2019%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ealready%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20anvil.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202021%2C%20soon%20after%20the%20prime%20minister%20announced%20the%20policy%2C%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20there%20was%20a%20lack%20of%20scientific%20consensus%20whether%20mandatory%20fortification%20works%20effectively%2C%20or%20would%20not%20lead%20to%20side%20effects.%20But%20the%20FSSAI%E2%80%99s%20own%20scientific%20experts%20cautioned%20against%20it.%20They%20said%20it%20should%20not%20be%20perceived%20as%20a%20panacea%2C%20and%20there%20was%20potential%20for%20excess%20intake%2C%20such%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20cure%20then%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS000291652200452X%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebecomes%20the%20malady%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20Section%2013%20of%20the%20Food%20Safety%20and%20Standards%20Act%2C%202006%2C%20the%20FSSAI%20hosts%2021%20%E2%80%9CScientific%20Panels%E2%80%9D.%20These%20panels%20develop%20standards%2C%20and%20provide%20scientific%20opinions%20to%20the%20food%20authority.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1909687%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESP-18%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20the%20scientific%20panel%20on%20Nutrition%20and%20Fortification.%20At%20least%20two%20former%20members%20of%20%E2%80%9CSP-18%E2%80%9D%20were%20publicly%20critical%20of%20the%20approach%20of%20mandatory%20fortification%20of%20food%20as%20a%20solution%20to%20anaemia.%20Dr%20Anura%20Kurpad%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Scientific%20Committee%20of%20the%20FSSAI%20till%202022.%20Dr%20HPS%20Sachdev%20was%20at%20the%20time%20of%20writing%20the%20Chairperson%2C%20FSSAI%20Expert%20Committee%201%20for%20%E2%80%9CApproval%20of%20Non-specified%20Food%20and%20Food%20Ingredients%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20answer%20does%20not%20lie%20in%20the%20techno-utopia%20of%20food%20reductionism%2C%20seductive%20as%20it%20is%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20stated%20in%20an%20op-ed%20titled%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Frice-fortification-programme-iron-anaemia-7470938%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20Flawed%20Recipe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20in%20The%20Indian%20Express%3A%20%E2%80%9C..The%20benefits%20derived%20from%20the%20nutrients%20in%20whole%20foods%20are%20greater%20than%20the%20sum%20of%20their%20parts.%E2%80%9D%20Further%2C%20they%20warned%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmeals%20in%20pill%20form%E2%80%9D%20have%20been%20ranked%20by%20the%20Time%20magazine%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthird%20in%20the%20top%2010%20failed%20futuristic%20predictions.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20series%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fblogs%2Fvoices%2Fwhy-rice-fortification-is-not-just-unnecessary-but-potentially-risky%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Earticles%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20press%20and%20journal%20articles%2C%20Dr%20Kurpad%20and%20Dr%20Sachdev%20questioned%20the%20rationale%20of%20the%20proposal%20of%20feeding%20iron-fortified%20rice%20compulsorily%20as%20a%20way%20to%20reduce%20anaemia%20when%20the%20health%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20recent%20Comprehensive%20National%20Nutrition%20Survey(CNNS)%20showed%20that%20iron%20deficiency%20causes%20less%20than%20half%20of%20all%20anaemia%20cases%20in%20India%20(sub-clinical%20infections%20being%20among%20other%20reasons).%20They%20argued%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20nutrition%20policy%20could%20not%20be%20based%20on%20the%20assumption%20that%20the%20causes%20of%20anaemia%20were%20same%20in%20all%20its%20diverse%20regions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20enumerated%20serious%20concerns%20arising%20as%20India%20already%20has%20an%20iron%20supplementation%20program%20through%20use%20of%20iron%20tablets%2C%20and%20iron%20is%20also%20added%20to%20salt%20and%20flour%20given%20in%20public%20schemes.%20Both%20physicians%20flagged%20that%20fortifying%20rice%20too%20with%20iron%20would%20lead%20to%20over-layering%2C%20it%20could%20cause%20harm.%20Instead%2C%20they%20argued%2C%20the%20government%20ought%20to%20focus%20on%20supporting%20a%20diverse%20diet%20such%20as%20shown%20empirically%20by%20scientific%20trials%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosone%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0248698%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKoraput%20and%20Wardh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20support%20adequate%20intake%20of%20fresh%20food.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20his%20office%20in%20Sitaram%20Bhartia%20hospital%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Dr%20HPS%20Sachdev%2C%20a%20paediatrician%2C%20stated%20that%20the%20decision%20to%20mandatorily%20fortify%20staples%20was%20not%20recommended%20by%20the%20FSSAI%E2%80%99s%20panel%20on%20fortification%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20found%20about%20it%20(mandatory%20fortification%20of%20rice%20in%20the%20PDS)%20after%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20speech%20on%20August%2015%2C%202021%E2%80%9D%20said%20Dr%20Sachdev.%20He%20said%20the%20panel%20had%20been%20asked%20to%20helped%20set%20the%20standards%20for%20voluntary%20fortification%2C%20not%20mandatory.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20(FSSAI)%20panel%E2%80%99s%20work%20was%20limited%20to%20create%20standards%20to%20prevent%20harm%20from%20fortification%2C%20that%20is%20what%20should%20be%20the%20content%2C%20the%20standards%2C%20additives%2C%20in%20what%20concentration.%20This%20decision%20(to%20fortify%20the%20poor%E2%80%99s%20rations%20compulsorily)%20did%20not%20come%20from%20the%20scientific%20panel.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EResponding%20to%20a%20question%20about%20these%20scientists%E2%80%99%20published%20concerns%2C%20Inoshi%20Sharma%2C%20a%20bureaucrat%20then%20executive%20director%20of%20FFRC%2C%20told%20this%20reporter%2C%20in%20March%202023%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20a%20government%20summit%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20scientists%20are%20ex-members%2C%20and%20are%20free%20to%20say%20anything%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERTI%20documents%20show%20that%20in%20initial%20meetings%20on%20planning%20implementation%20of%20the%20scheme%2C%20on%20January%2016%2C%202019%2C%20the%20Director%20(FFRC)%20described%20the%20role%20of%20FSSAI%20to%20include%20setting%20standards%2C%20creating%20regulations%2C%20use%20of%20only%20%E2%80%9Cplant%20sources%20for%20Vitamin%20D%E2%80%9D%20(thus%2C%20ensuring%20vegetarianism)%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Ccreating%20demand%20in%20open%20market%20for%2C%20and%20linking%20government%20safety%20net%20programs%20to%20fortified%20supplies.%E2%80%9D%20the%20FFRC%20Director%20made%20recommendations%20on%20the%20central%20government%E2%80%99s%20fortified%20rice%20scheme%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20should%20not%20be%20an%20end%20date%20attached%20to%20the%20scheme%E2%80%9D.%20In%20January%202021%2C%20a%20memo%20of%20expenditure%20of%20the%20finance%20committee%20of%20the%20ministry%20of%20food%20and%20civil%20supplies%20too%20referred%20to%20it%20as%20%E2%80%9Cproposed%20to%20be%20an%20ongoing%20perpetually%20all%20over%20the%20country%E2%80%9D%20scheme.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20precisely%20one%20of%20the%20concerns%20the%20UN%20Food%20rapporteur%20Schutter%20outlined%20in%20embarking%20on%20such%20schemes.%20Schutter%20categorically%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erecommended%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20such%20schemes%20must%20have%20%E2%80%9Can%20end%20date%E2%80%9D%2C%20to%20avoid%20creating%20corporate%20dependencies%3A%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CSolutions%20that%20rely%20on%20imported%20technologies%20and%20products%20may%20create%20long%20term%20dependencies%20for%20the%20communities%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20warned.%20Giving%20the%20example%20of%20GAIN%2C%20which%20partners%20with%20companies%20to%20reach%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20bottom%20of%20the%20pyramid%2C%E2%80%9D%20or%20potential%20customers%20who%20are%20%E2%80%9Ctoo%20poor%20to%20constitute%20a%20solvent%20market%20in%20the%20short%20term%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20stated%20that%20any%20such%20intervention%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20include%20a%20clear%20exit%20strategy%20to%20empower%20communities%20to%20feed%20themselves.%E2%80%9D%20In%20contrast%2C%20Indian%20policy%20makers%20allowed%20lobbying%20in%20FFRC%20against%20having%20such%20an%20end%20date%20of%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161455%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.14.04.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161455%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.14.04.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161455%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.14.04-300x204.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161455%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.14.04-1024x695.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686237%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22814%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAn%20Adivasi%20farmer%20showing%20a%20local%20effort%20at%20making%20compost%20in%20a%20village%20in%20Chakulia%20in%20Jharkhand%E2%80%99s%20East%20Singhbhum.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIdentifying%20an%20end%20date%20for%20mandatory%20fortification%20requires%20benchmarks%20and%20systematic%20evaluation.%20A%20letter%20by%20Alok%20Kumar%20Adviser%20(Nutrition)%20at%20NITI%20Aayog%20dated%20February%2014%2C%202019%20had%20stated%20the%20goal%20of%20fortification%20was%20%E2%80%9Creducing%20stunting%20by%202%25%20per%20year%2C%20under-nutrition%20by%202%25%20per%20year%2C%20anaemia%20by%203%25%20per%20year%2C%20and%20low%20birth%20weight%20by%202%25%20per%20year%E2%80%9D.%20On%20paper%20the%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20aim%20is%20to%20end%20anaemia.%20But%20in%20the%20districts%20where%20the%20schemes%20is%20implemented%2C%20no%20baseline%20evaluation%20%E2%80%93%20an%20initial%20assessment%20to%20measure%20the%20later%20changes%20against%20%E2%80%93%20was%20done.%20And%20as%20stated%20earlier%2C%20the%20government%20has%20this%20year%20discontinued%20the%20previous%20surveying%20of%20anaemia%20at%20the%20level%20of%20districts%20itself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20plan%20document%20recommended%20concurrent%20evaluation%2C%20setting%20up%20of%20central%20and%20state%20monitoring%20units%2C%20in%20a%20RTI%20reply%2C%20the%20food%20ministry%20stated%20that%20a%20central%20unit%20had%20been%20set%20up.%20It%20stated%20that%20the%20ministry%20did%20not%20have%20information%20on%20if%20states%20where%20the%20scheme%20is%20implemented%20among%20communities%2C%20have%20set%20up%20the%20monitoring%20units.%20Ministry%20officials%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20question%20about%20an%20end%20date%20of%20the%20fortification%20scheme.%20Meanwhile%2C%20it%20is%20set%20to%20be%20scaled%20up%20universally%20by%20March%202024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20policy%20to%20compulsorily%20fortify%20food%20has%20no%20clear%20end%20date%2C%20and%20it%20is%20continuing%20and%20even%20expanding%2C%20the%20lobbying%20hub%20FFRC%2C%20that%20till%20recently%20took%20credit%20for%20it%2C%20has%20been%20scrubbed%20off%20the%20Internet.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20activist%20groups%20ASHA%20and%20Right%20to%20Food%20Campaign%20published%20a%20report%20this%20February%20highlighting%20the%20potential%20conflicts%20of%20interest%20in%20the%20operating%20of%20FFRC%20within%20the%20FSSAI.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20social%20media%20handles%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eshowing%20the%20presence%20of%20these%20organisations%20in%20government%20meetings%20and%20policy%20setting%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehave%20been%20deleted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20This%20reporter%20accessed%20the%20FSSAI%20fortification%20website%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year%20in%20February%20when%20it%20mentioned%20FFRC%20and%20its%20team.%20On%20searching%20for%20it%20after%20April%2C%20the%20FFRC%20page%20was%20no%20longer%20accessible.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20530px)%2085vw%2C%20530px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24215024%2FFB-FFRC.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24215024%2FFB-FFRC.png%20869w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24215024%2FFB-FFRC-300x204.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686291%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22361%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20deleted%20FFRC%20Facebook%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInoshi%20Sharma%2C%20the%20former%20director%20of%20FFRC%2C%20told%20this%20reporter%20that%20the%20agreement%20between%20FSSAI%20and%20Tata%20Trusts%20was%20for%20three%20years.%20As%20per%20news%20reports%2C%20FFRC%20was%20launched%20in%202016%2C%20though%20as%20per%20Sharma%20it%20had%20been%20closed%20down%20after%20five%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20a%20three%20year%20agreement%20with%20Tata%20Trusts.%20FFRC%20closed%20down%20in%20August%202021%2C%E2%80%9D%20Inoshi%20Sharma%2C%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20March%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20a%20government%20summit%20in%20March%20while%20she%20was%20listed%20as%20executive%20director%20of%20FFRC%20on%20the%20FSSAI%20website.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20FSSAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20further%20questions%20on%20details%20of%20its%20terms%20of%20engagement%20with%20FFRC%20partners%2C%20when%20reporter%20visited%20the%20FSSAI%20building%20in%20August%20and%20September%202023%20with%20follow%20up%20questions%2C%20the%20FSSAI%20staff%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9CFFRC%20no%20longer%20exists%2C%20and%20only%20the%20standards%20division%20works%20on%20fortification%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIts%20social%20media%20pages%20which%20were%20active%20till%20earlier%20this%20year%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fffrc_fssai%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewere%20deleted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20this%20year%2C%20after%20public%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fkkuruganti%2Fstatus%2F1626163245508857856%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecriticism%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20around%20its%20opaqueness%20by%20ASHA%20activists.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20590px)%2085vw%2C%20590px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161730%2F15.1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22590%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161730%2F15.1.png%20590w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161730%2F15.1-300x127.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686239%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22249%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFFRC%E2%80%99s%20social%20media%20pages%20were%20deleted%20after%20activists%20criticised%20the%20embedding%20of%20it%20as%20a%20lobbying%20hub%20inside%20India%E2%80%99s%20food%20regulatory%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%9CLargest%20market%20in%20anaemia%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20outcomes%20on%20nutrition%20are%20not%20clear%20yet%2C%20the%20profits%20for%20large%20industry%20associated%20with%20fortification%20have%20grown.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20first%20companies%20to%20manufacture%20fortified%20rice%20kernels%20in%20India%20is%20JVS%20Foods%20Private%20Limited%2C%20which%20runs%20its%20factories%20in%20Jaipur%2C%20Rajasthan.%20In%20India%2C%20JVS%20Foods%20is%20one%20of%20the%20first%20facilities%20and%20the%20only%20facility%20manufacturing%20fortified%20rice%20kernels%20that%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgpf.gainhealth.org%2Fsuppliers%2Fcurrent-suppliers%23pane6%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecertified%20by%20GAIN%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20founded%20body%20promoting%20food%20industry-led%20solutions%20to%20hunger.%20Its%20related%20firm%20Wella%20Nutrologicals%20%E2%80%93%20both%20factories%20in%20Sitapura%20are%20a%20few%20meters%20apart%20%E2%80%93%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgpf.gainhealth.org%2Fsuppliers%2Fcurrent-suppliers%23pane6%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecertified%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20GAIN%20in%20dry%20premix.%20JVS%20supplied%20fortified%20kernels%20to%20Jharkhand%2C%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20poorest%20states%20with%20highest%20rates%20of%20anaemia%20and%20malnutrition%2C%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20pilot%20in%20the%20state%20for%20the%20scheme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESenior%20managers%20at%20JVS%20Foods%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20how%20their%20market%20and%20profits%20had%20grown%20manifold.%20Abhishek%20Jain%2C%20a%20senior%20production%20manager%2C%20and%20head%20of%20marketing%2C%20JVS%20Foods%20said%20they%20started%20production%20about%20seven%20years%20ago%20making%20barely%20300%20kilograms%20of%20fortified%20rice%20kernels%20a%20year%2C%20and%20now%20produced%20200%2C000%20kilo(200%20tonnes)%20a%20day%20in%20the%20peak%20demand%20which%20lasted%20eight%20months%20a%20year%2C%20a%20massive%20increase.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COur%20first%20batch%20was%20bought%20by%20the%20NGO%20Akshaypatra%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jain%20said%2C%20at%20his%20factory%20in%20Jaipur.%20%E2%80%9CInitially%20it%20was%20mostly%20only%20private%20or%20NGO%20buyers.%20Then%2C%20the%20government%20came%20in.%20Now%2C%20primarily%20the%20government%20procures%20this.%20In%20this%20current%20financial%20year%2C%20we%20sold%203%2C000%20tonnes%20rice%20kernels%20to%20Haryana%20government%20alone.%E2%80%9D%20As%20FRK%20markets%20grow%20so%20does%20the%20market%20for%20pre-mixes.%20JVS%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20IT%20makes%20FRK%20and%20it%20imports%20vitamins%20premix%20via%20the%20Dutch%20firm%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20vitamin%20maker%2C%20Royal%20DSM%E2%80%99s%20unit%20in%20India%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20imported%20it%20from%20DSM%20Singapore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJain%20further%20stated%20that%20PATH%2C%20the%20American%20NGO%20funded%20by%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20persuaded%20them%20to%20start%20supplying%20fortificants%20as%20a%20substantive%20business%20domestically%20and%20abroad%20opportunity%2C%20and%20which%20also%20led%20it%20to%20start%20pre-mix%20imports.%20%E2%80%9CAmong%20the%20first%20people%20to%20come%20to%20us%20was%20PATH%2C%E2%80%9D%20recounted%20Jain.%20%E2%80%9CAbout%20seven%20years%20back%2C%20they%20came%20and%20told%20us%20about%20the%20making%20of%20Fortified%20Rice%20Kernels.%20They%20told%20us%20that%20this%20is%20business%20of%20the%20future%2C%20and%20asked%20us%3A%20will%20you%20take%20part%20in%20this%20business%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fin.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fruchika-chugh-sachdeva-a2717015%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERuchika(Chugh%20Sachdeva%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20(who%20is%20currently%20the%20BMGF%20nutrition%20lead%20in%20its%20India%20country%20office)%2C%20who%20at%20that%20time%20worked%20in%20PATH%2C%20led%20this%20work%20with%20us.%20Their%20staff%20visited%20us%2C%20and%20we%20said%20alright%2C%20what%20be%20our%20costs%3F%20They%20told%20us%20that%20this%20market%20was%20expanding.%20In%20Vietnam%2C%20fortification%20was%20being%20mandatory%20in%20wheat%20flour%2C%20in%20Oceanic%20countries%20100%25%20fortification%20was%20becoming%20mandatory.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPATH%20told%20us%20that%20the%20future%20of%20this%20market%20lies%20in%20India%2C%20because%20there%20is%20such%20widespread%20anaemia%20in%20India.%20In%20fact%2C%2090%20percent%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20anaemia%20is%20in%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jain%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161852%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.17.43.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161852%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.17.43.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161852%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.17.43-300x189.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24161852%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-4.17.43-1024x645.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686241%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22756%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIndustry%20players%20such%20as%20JVS%20Foods%20say%20there%20is%20an%20explosive%20growth%20in%20the%20market%20for%20therapeutic%20food%20and%20fortificants%20in%20India%2C%20and%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20added%20that%20after%20they%20agreed%2C%20they%20accompanied%20PATH%20staff%20to%20China%20to%20select%20and%20purchase%20machines%2C%20equipment%20in%202016-17.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20went%20with%20PATH%20to%20China%2C%20and%20we%20spent%20around%20eight%20days%20there.%20PATH%20helped%20us%20meet%208-9%20manufacturers%20there%20who%20make%20the%20equipment.%20Then%20we%20bought%20the%20first%20machine%E2%80%A6It%20was%20PATH%20that%20did%20everything%20with%20us%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPATH%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20an%20emailed%20question%20on%20the%20claims%20by%20JVS%20Foods%20staff.%20Ruchika%20Chugh%20Sachdeva%2C%20the%20BMGF%E2%80%99s%20nutrition%20lead%20in%20its%20India%2C%20declined%20an%20interview%20when%20this%20reporter%20reached%20out%20to%20her%20on%20her%20phone.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENourishing%20profits%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20lobbying%20on%20food%20fortification%20has%20parallels%20with%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20food%20and%20farming%20sectors%20of%20other%20poor%20and%20developing%20nations.%20One%20of%20the%20biggest%20corporations%20in%20this%20sector%20is%20the%20Netherlands%E2%80%99%20Royal%20DSM%2C%20which%20was%20a%20chemical%20company%20for%20most%20of%20its%20history.%20It%20bought%20the%20vitamin%20division%20of%20Swiss%20healthcare%20conglomerate%20Roche%20in%202003%2C%20and%20is%20now%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20maker%20of%20vitamins.%20In%202007%2C%20it%20became%20a%20partner%20of%20the%20World%20Food%20Programme%2C%20supplying%20the%20WFP%20with%20micronutrient%20powder.%20It%20has%20made%20nutrition%20its%20central%20business%2C%20especially%20in%20poor%20countries.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20Rwanda%2C%20it%20sources%20soy%20from%20small%20farmers%20and%20gives%20it%20to%20Rwandan%20government%20processed%20as%20a%20micronutrient%20fortified%20porridge.%20It%20refers%20to%20the%20facility%20as%20the%20largest%20such%20nutrition%20factory%20sites%20in%20East%20Africa.%20In%20India%2C%20it%20exports%20vitamin%20pre-mix%20to%20firms%20such%20as%20JVS%2C%20and%20runs%20fortified%20rice%20kernel%20blending%20and%20processing%20facilities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFood%20industry%20such%20as%20DSM%2C%20other%20agro-chemicals%20and%20pharmaceutical%20companies%20view%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.finchandbeak.com%2F1264%2Ffresh-partners-global-platform-for-food.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EUSD%202.3%20trillion%20business%20opportunity%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20in%20implementation%20of%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20related%20to%20ending%20hunger%20by%202030.%20Large%20aid%20agencies%20support%20this.%20For%20example%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20Glasgow%20climate%20summit%20in%202021%2C%20the%20US%20government%20released%20a%20new%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usaid.gov%2Fnews-information%2Fpress-releases%2Fsep-23-2021-administrator-power-announces-5-billion-food-systems-investments-combat-global-hunger-and-malnutrition%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estrategy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20framing%20nutrition%20as%20a%20technical%20problem%20for%20agro-processors%20to%20solve.%20It%20stated%20it%20will%20invest%20USD%2038%20million%20in%20five%20years%20to%20expand%20%E2%80%9Clarge%20scale%20food%20fortification%E2%80%9D%20partnering%20with%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20GAIN%2C%20UNICEF.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20business%20model%20approach%20to%20hunger%20assumes%20malnutrition%20is%20a%20simple%20problem%20with%20a%20technical%20fix.%20By%20not%20taking%20farmers%E2%80%99%20role%20in%20ecology%20of%20food%20production%20seriously%2C%20and%20not%20addressing%20structural%20causes%20such%20as%20global%20trade%2C%20financial%20agreements%20that%20often%20restrict%20a%20country%20from%20supporting%20local%20smallholder%20farmers%2C%20such%20corporations%20and%20large%20aid%20agencies%20reduce%20the%20complexities%20of%20nutrition%20and%20dietary%20health%20to%20a%20process%20of%20adding%20in%20vitamins%2C%20a%20problem%20to%20earn%20profit%20off%20while%20solving.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20last%2020%20years%2C%20the%20dialogue%20has%20moved%20from%20how%20to%20enable%20access%20to%20good%20and%20healthy%20diets%20into%20silos%2C%20such%20as%20lack%20of%20micronutrients%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Dr%20Arun%20Gupta%2C%20who%20convenes%20the%20network%20Nutrition%20Advocacy%20in%20Public%20Interest%20(NAPi).%20%E2%80%9CI%20do%20not%20blame%20the%20corporations%20for%20their%20push.%20Eg.%20if%20they%20are%20making%20vitamin%20A%20or%20iron%2C%20they%20will%20want%20to%20sell%20those%20products.%20But%20when%20they%20start%20influencing%20government%20policy%20and%20lobbying%20for%20the%20use%20of%20these%2C%20then%20we%20ought%20to%20ask%20what%20is%20happening%2C%20in%20whose%20interests%3F%E2%80%9D%20Gupta%20recounted%20that%20he%20along%20with%20other%20members%20of%20NAPi%20had%20staged%20a%20public%20protest%20in%20central%20Delhi%20when%20GAIN%2C%C2%A0%20which%20co-chairs%20its%20SUN%20business%20network%20promoting%20industrial%20processed%20food%20along%20with%20DSM%20the%20vitamin-maker%2C%20first%20started%20lobbying%20with%20members%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20parliament%20in%202008.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20held%20placards%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%99GAIN%20is%20a%20pain!%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98GAIN%20go%20back!%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20he%20recounted.%20%E2%80%9CAt%20that%20time%2C%20we%20succeeded%20in%20convincing%20a%20few%20MPs%2C%20senior%20bureaucrats%20to%20not%20get%20taken%20in%20with%20this%20systematic%20push%20to%20fortified%20foods.%20But%2C%20this%20time%2C%20their%20lobbying%20has%20succeeded.%20It%20will%20lead%20to%20irreversible%20changes%20in%20our%20food%20and%20health%20systems.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162026%2F17-woman-selling-veggies.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162026%2F17-woman-selling-veggies.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162026%2F17-woman-selling-veggies-300x198.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162026%2F17-woman-selling-veggies-1024x676.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686242%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22792%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPublic%20health%20experts%20say%20fortification%20will%20disrupt%20small%20industry%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20food%20system%20which%20allows%20local%20producers%20to%20sell%20diverse%2C%20fresh%20vegetables%2C%20meat%2C%20eggs%2C%20whole%20grains.%20Photo%3A%20Anumeha%20Yadav%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPublic%20nutritionists%20have%20traced%20how%20in%20the%20last%20few%20decades%2C%20certain%20factory-made%20micronutrients%20were%20advanced%20as%20an%20antidote%20for%20anaemia%20and%20malnutrition%2C%20even%20without%20complete%20evidence.%20Over%20time%2C%20large%20aid%20agencies%20priortised%20this%20approach%20over%20other%20diversified%20food-based%20strategies.%20In%20a%20well-known%20paper%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fworldnutritionjournal.org%2Findex.php%2Fwn%2Farticle%2Fview%2F570%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Great%20Vitamin%20A%20Fiasco%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20published%20in%202010%2C%20Michael%20Latham%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20nutrition%20at%20Cornell%20University%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eand%20a%20member%20of%20International%20Vitamin%20A%20Consultative%20Group%20(IVACG)%2C%20which%20is%20a%20network%20of%20experts%20and%20law%20makers%20initially%20created%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20United%20States%20International%20Aid%20Agency(USAID)%20in%201975%2C%20traces%20how%20the%20advocacy%20by%20large%20aid%20agencies%2C%20including%20USAID%2C%20pushed%20for%20mandatory%20supplementation%20with%20vitamin%20A%20capsules.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELatham%20writes%20about%20the%20history%20of%20the%20push%20to%20addressing%20malnutrition%20by%20splitting%20it%20into%20micronutrients%2C%20and%20the%20promotion%20of%20the%20a%20%E2%80%9Chidden%20hunger%E2%80%9D%20concept%2C%20even%20where%20evidence%20for%20its%20efficacy%20was%20incomplete.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%98Three%20micronutrients%20were%20%E2%80%9Csingled%20out%E2%80%9D%20as%20deserving%20particular%20attention%3A%20vitamin%20A%2C%20iron%2C%20and%20iodine.%20Although%20useful%20in%20prioritizing%20problems%20and%20drawing%20attention%20to%20the%20need%20for%20action%2C%20the%20identification%20of%20these%20particular%20micronutrients%20was%20somewhat%20arbitrary%2C%20based%20on%20an%20interpretation%20of%20data%20available%20at%20that%20time%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20quotes%20David%20Alnwick%2C%20of%20the%20UNICEF%20micronutrients%20programme%2C%20in%201990.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%20the%20push%20towards%20this%20by%20aid%20agencies%2C%20he%20identified%20that%20a%20major%20driving%20force%20was%20industry%2C%20which%20is%20highly%20concentrated.%20Between%201999%20and%202001%2C%20eight%20vitamin%20corporations%2C%20including%20Roche(which%20sold%20its%20business%20to%20Royal%20DSM)%20and%20BASF%20had%20to%20pay%20millions%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1999%2F11%2F04%2Fbusiness%2F1.1-billion-to-settle-suit-on-vitamins.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efines%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20US%20as%20well%20as%20in%20Europe%20after%20an%20enquiry%20found%20that%20throughout%20the%201990s%2C%20these%20corporations%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fmoney%2F2001%2Fnov%2F21%2Fpersonalfinancenews.europeanunion%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eacted%20as%20a%20cartel%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20colluding%20to%20fix%20prices%20for%20synthetic%20vitamins.%20Despite%20this%20rap%2C%20their%20markets%20and%20profits%20have%20grown%20The%20vitamins%20market%20worth%20USD%203%20billion%20a%20year%20in%201999%2C%20in%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20grew%20nearly%2015%20times%20to%20over%20US%20%24%2045%20billion%20last%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20activists%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20concern%20is%20that%20industrial%20fortification%20shifts%20focus%20away%20from%20food-based%20approaches.%20In%20his%20paper%2C%20Latham%20too%20shows%20how%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20vitamin%20supplementation%20was%20conceived%20at%20the%20UN%20initially%20as%20only%20as%20a%20temporary%20measure%2C%20pending%20dietary%20improvements.%20But%20from%201990s%2C%20it%20dominated%20all%20other%20means%20to%20improve%20vitamin%20A%20status.%20In%20IVACG%20meetings%2C%20he%20recounted%2C%20the%20findings%20of%20studies%20showing%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20food-based%20approaches%20such%20as%20eating%20green%20leaves%2C%20common%20tropical%20fruits%20to%20change%20vitamin%20status%20were%20either%20not%20accepted%20for%20presentation%2C%20or%20given%20little%20attention.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202006%2C%20the%20IVACG%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20International%20Nutritional%20anaemia%20Consultative%20Group%20(INACG)%2C%20both%20of%20which%20were%20then%20funded%20by%20USAID%2C%20were%20incorporated%20into%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Micronutrient%20Forum%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20a%20network%20to%20focus%20on%20several%20micronutrients%2C%20now%20substantively(50%25%20of%20its%20earmarked%20funds%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20funded%20by%20the%20Gates%20Foundation.%20It%20holds%20global%20conferences.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162141%2F18-Micronutrient-Forum-funds-of-gates.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162141%2F18-Micronutrient-Forum-funds-of-gates.png%20682w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162141%2F18-Micronutrient-Forum-funds-of-gates-300x42.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686243%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%2295%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20earlier%20USAID%20groups%20on%20anaemia%20and%20vitamin%20A%20deficiencies%20are%20now%20the%20%E2%80%9CMicronutrient%20Forum%E2%80%9D%20which%20have%20substantive%20funds%20from%20BMGF%20and%20a%20few%20corporate%20sponsors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELatham%20had%20criticised%20its%20%E2%80%98gold%E2%80%99%20corporate%20sponsors%20of%20its%202009%20convening%20were%20Coca-Cola%20and%20Pepsi-Co.%20At%20its%20more%20recent%20%E2%80%9CConnected%20Conference%E2%80%9D%20in%20Thailand%20in%202020%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmicronutrientforum.org%2Fabout-us%2Four-partners%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esponsors%20included%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20ADOB(which%20makes%20fertilizers)%2C%20BASF%20(which%20makes%20chemical%20fertilizers%20as%20well%20as%20synthetic%20vitamins)%2C%20Sight%20and%20Life%20(a%20non-profit%20which%20continues%20to%20be%20funded%20by%20vitamin%20company%20Royal%20DSM%20and%20half%20its%20board%20members%20are%20DSM%20personnel)%2C%20ContractPharma(food%20supplements%20firm)%2C%20and%20SQM%2C%20a%20Chilean%20mining%20giant%2C%20among%20others.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20was%20the%20evidence%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20few%20months%20before%20the%20FSSAI%20had%20notified%20standards%20for%20voluntary%20fortification%20of%20staples%20for%20industry%2C%20the%20policy%20discussion%20had%20veered%20towards%20anaemia%20as%20a%20problem%20to%20be%20solved%20by%20fortification.%20In%20a%20letter%20to%20all%20states%20of%20June%208%2C%202018%2C%20then%20NITI%20Aayog%20CEO%20Amitabh%20Kant%20stated%20that%20National%20Nutrition%20Mission%20christened%20POSHAN%20by%20Modi%20on%20March%208%2C%202018%20%E2%80%9Cneeds%20to%20address%20macro%20and%20micronutrients.%E2%80%9D%20He%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9C70%25%20Indians%20are%20eating%20less%20than%20half%20RDA%20daily%20needs)%20of%20micronutrients..one%20way%20is%20by%20promoting%20local%20millets%2C%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%2C%E2%80%9D%20but%20added%2C%20these%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20out%20of%20reach%20of%20the%20poorest%20families.%E2%80%9D%20Instead%20of%20detailing%20what%20could%20the%20government%20do%20to%20support%20the%20poorest%20families%20to%20eat%20local%20millets%2C%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%2C%20Kant%20pivots%20that%20%E2%80%9Ca%20low%20cost%20intervention%E2%80%9D%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cmandating%20fortification%20of%20food%20staples.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20the%20National%20Food%20Security%20Act%2C%20passed%20in%202013%20after%20years%20of%20demands%20by%20groups%20such%20as%20the%20Right%20to%20Food%20Campaign%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdfpd.gov.in%2FIntroduction.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexpand%20India%E2%80%99s%20food%20safety%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20net%2C%20covers%20813%20million%20citizens.%20Under%20this%2C%20the%20union%20government%20distributes%20600%20lakh%20metric%20tonnes%20grains%20annually%20to%20the%20poor%2C%20including%20350%20lakh%20metric%20tonnes%20rice.%20Starting%202019%2C%20the%20food%20ministry%20began%20pilots%20to%20give%20fortified%20rice%20in%2015%20districts%20where%20it%20supplied%20five%20kilos%20grains%20per%20person%20per%20month.%20It%20proposed%20giving%20fortified%20rice%20first%20in%20children%E2%80%99s%20schemes%2C%20then%20in%20the%20rations%20scheme%20in%20112%20poorest%20districts%2C%20followed%20by%20250%20malnourished%20districts%20by%202021-2022.%20Around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20NITI%20Ayog%20file%20noting%20show%20its%20officials%20recommended%2C%20these%20250%20%E2%80%9Cmalnourished%E2%80%9D%20districts%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20re-worded%E2%80%9D%2C%20calling%20them%20%E2%80%9CHigh%20Burden%20Districts%E2%80%9D%20instead.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20pilots%20did%20not%20go%20well.%20They%20did%20not%20even%20take%20off%20for%20the%20next%20two%20years%20in%20eight%20of%20the%2015%20identified%20districts.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20pilot%20scheme%20has%20been%20rolled%20out%20only%20in%207%20out%20of%2015%20states.%20Over%20a%203%20year%20period%20there%20has%20been%20a%20lukewarm%20response%2C%E2%80%9D%20Joint%20Secretary(PFS)%2C%20DoE%20again%20stated%20in%20the%20minutes%20of%20the%20meeting%20of%20the%20Expenditure%20Finance%20Committee%20in%20September%202021.%20As%20a%20report%20by%20The%20Reporters%E2%80%99%20Collective%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reporters-collective.in%2Ftrc%2Fdespite-internal-red-flags-and-uncertain-science-modi-govt-serves-fortified-rice-to-indias-poor%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efirst%20showed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20earlier%2C%20on%20October%209%2C%202019%2C%20the%20department%20of%20expenditure%E2%80%99s%20note%20replying%20to%20a%20food%20ministry%20letter%20of%20September%2012%2C%202019%20cautioned%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20proposal%20for%20universal%20roll-out%20of%20the%20scheme%20from%202023-24%20without%20studying%20the%20output%2Foutcome%20and%20evaluation%20of%20pilot%20project%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20pre-mature%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%E2%80%9D%20But%20the%20other%20government%20wings%2C%20the%20FSSAI%20and%20the%20ministry%20of%20food%20and%20civil%20supplies%20pressed%20ahead%2C%20scaling%20up%20the%20pilots.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162245%2F19-warning-by-Finance-ministry.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162245%2F19-warning-by-Finance-ministry.png%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162245%2F19-warning-by-Finance-ministry-300x81.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686244%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22243%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Expenditure%2C%20in%20an%20office%20memorandum%2C%20warned%20that%20universalising%20fortified%20rice%20supply%20without%20first%20studying%20the%20pilot%E2%80%99s%20outcomes%20is%20premature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAddressing%20a%20seminar%20in%20October%202021%2C%20Sudhanshu%20Pandey%2C%20the%20then%20secretary%20of%20food%20and%20civil%20supplies%20department%2C%20acknowledged%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20pilots%2C%20while%20justifying%20why%20they%20were%20still%20scaled%20up.%20Pandey%20explained%20that%20the%20pilots%20lacked%20scale%20as%20the%20production%20of%20kernels%20was%20not%20there%2C%20further%2C%20crucial%20laboratories%20to%20test%20micronutrients%20were%20missing.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20were%20fundamental%20problems%20with%20the%20pilot%E2%80%A6the%20pilot%20were%20purely%20logistics%20and%20supply%20side%20related%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Pandey.%20In%20conducting%20the%20pilots%2C%20Pandey%20said%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20nearly%20all%20the%20pieces%20for%20the%20policy%20were%20missing%20%E2%80%93%20he%20named%20the%20supply%20of%20fortified%20rice%20kernels%2C%20the%20micronutrient%20mix%2C%20that%20machinery%20to%20make%20and%20blend%20the%20kernels%20lacked%20standardisation%2C%20and%20said%20that%20what%20made%20it%20more%20challenging%20was%20the%20sheer%20diversity%20of%20rice%20grain%20varieties%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20circular%20logic%2C%20Pandey%20explained%20that%20the%20officials%20saw%20that%20what%20they%20were%20proposing%20could%20not%20be%20done%2C%20and%20so%20they%20scaled%20it%20up%2C%20in%20the%20process%20of%20assuring%20the%20producers%20of%20a%20fixed%20market%2C%20to%20make%20the%20scheme%20a%20reality%20despite%20the%20lack%20of%20progress%20in%20pilots.%20The%20infrastructure%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cthreshold%20level%20and%20maturity%20scale%E2%80%9D%20were%20missing%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20ecosystem%20is%20not%20in%20place%E2%80%9D%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9CThe%20scale%20was%20not%20happening%E2%80%A6unless%20we%20bring%20in%20certainty%20in%20the%20policy%20itself%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pandey%20concluded.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBecause%20the%20problems%20in%20quality%20of%20rice%20kernels%20have%20continued%20despite%20the%20attempts%20to%20standardize%20equipment%2C%20the%20government%20and%20its%20%E2%80%9Cdevelopment%20partners%E2%80%9D%20have%20since%20proposed%20further%20technical%20solutions%20within%20their%20approach%20of%20tech%20fixes%20to%20hunger.%20Abhishek%20Jain%20of%20JVS%20Foods%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20as%20quality%20issues%20of%20fortified%20rice%20kernels%2C%20unreliable%20micronutrient%20content%2C%20adulteration%20continued%20to%20weigh%20down%20the%20scheme%2C%20PATH%20visited%20their%20factory%20in%20Jaipur%20to%20collect%20data%20on%20creating%20an%20automated%20system%20and%20was%20working%20to%20create%20%E2%80%9Ctraceability%E2%80%9D%20of%20kernels%20back%20to%20manufacturers.%20Pandey%20in%20his%20address%20stated%20that%20they%20were%20working%20on%20mandatory%20%E2%80%9Cbarcoding%E2%80%9D%20gunny%20bags%20of%20rice.%20The%20same%20recommendation%20was%20reiterated%20by%20the%20NITI%20Ayog%20in%20its%20file%20noting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKavitha%20Kuruganti%2C%20an%20activist%20with%20ASHA%20advocating%20for%20sustainable%20farm%20livelihoods%20and%20farmers%E2%80%99%20rights%20said%20the%20government%20was%20adopting%20technical%20fixes%2C%20%E2%80%9Cas%20if%20it%20is%20cut%20from%20reality%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20latching%20on%20to%20silver%20bullet%20solutions%2C%20heavily%20influenced%20by%20entities%20such%20as%20the%20BMGF%2C%20PATH%2C%20but%20it%20cannot%20deny%20the%20complexities%20of%20development%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kuruganti%2C%20who%20investigated%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20scheme%20in%20Jharkhand%20and%20Chhattisgarh.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Modi%20government%20should%20instead%20have%20listened%20to%20members%20of%20its%20own%20regulatory%20panels.%20It%20should%20have%20learnt%20from%20the%20better%20food-based%20alternatives%20by%20state%20governments%2C%20such%20as%20Odisha%E2%80%99s%20decentralised%20procurement%20of%20nutritious%20millets%2C%20and%20its%20program%20encouraging%20kitchen%20gardens.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECapture%20of%20policy-making%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20queries%20about%20its%20role%2C%20its%20influence%20on%20the%20pilot%20expansion%20is%20explicit%20in%20government%20documents%2C%20which%20mention%20BMGF%20as%20well%20as%20its%20funded%20entities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20detailed%20implementation%20action%20plan%20will%20be%20developed%20for%20the%20pan%20India%20expansion%20of%20rice%20fortification%20with%20GAIN.%20GAIN%20has%20been%20chosen%20as%20the%20development%20partner%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebecause%20it%20has%20been%20chosen%20as%20the%20focal%20point%20for%20all%20the%20development%20partners%20by%20BMGF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20states%20a%20noting%20on%20August%2023%2C%202021%20by%20Vedeika%20Shekhar%2C%20an%20associate%20at%20NITI%20Aayog.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20note%20is%20further%20followed%20by%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%20development%20of%20action%20plan%20of%20universalization%20of%20fortification%2C%20we%20may%20collaborate%20with%20GAIN%20as%20it%20is%20country%20coordinator%20for%20rice%20fortification%20for%20all%20development%20partners.%E2%80%9D%20on%20same%20date%20as%20stated%20by%20Hemant%20Kumar%20Meena%2C%20a%20Deputy%20Secretary.%C2%A0%20The%20file%20noting%20on%20fortification%20further%20show%20Arvind%20Betigeri%2C%20who%20has%20been%20head%20of%20PATH%E2%80%99s%20rice%20fortification%20project%20in%20India%2C%20attended%20these%20NITI%20Aayog%20meetings%20as%20a%20senior%20consultant.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162306%2F20-NITI-File-BMGF.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22787%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162306%2F20-NITI-File-BMGF.png%20787w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162306%2F20-NITI-File-BMGF-300x181.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686245%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22475%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENITI%20Aayog%20in%20its%20file%20noting%20states%20choosing%20development%20partners%20as%20chosen%20by%20BMGF%20and%20GAIN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20its%20inter-ministerial%20correspondence%2C%20the%20union%20government%20justified%20the%20mandatory%20rice%20fortification%20with%20often%20inaccurate%2C%20or%20partially%20accurate%20claims.%20In%20January%202021%2C%20memo%20of%20expenditure%20finance%20committee%20of%20food%20and%20civil%20supplies%20ministry%20noted%20the%20aim%20of%20the%20scheme%20was%20reducing%20anaemia.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20as%20stated%20earlier%2C%20doctors%20on%20the%20FSSAI%20scientific%20panels%20such%20as%20Dr%20Sachdev%20said%20shown%20that%20the%20policy%20is%20not%20appropriate%20to%20address%20anaemia%20because%20nearly%20half%20the%20anaemia%20cases%20in%20India%20are%20not%20even%20from%20iron%20deficiency%2C%20but%20other%20causes.%20Yet%2C%20the%20food%20ministry%20argued%20for%20the%20policy%2C%20claiming%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20per%20WHO%2C%20rice%20fortification%20with%20vitamins%20and%20minerals%20including%20iron%20reduces%20risk%20of%20iron%20deficiency%20by%2035%25%20which%20leads%20to%20estimated%20GDP%20gain%20of%20about%20Rs%2049%2C800%20crore%20as%20per%20FSSAI.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20WHO%20guideline%20of%202018%20it%20relied%20on%2C%20however%2C%20had%20stated%20a%20more%20nuanced%20and%20somewhat%20different%20finding.%20It%20states%20that%20eating%20fortified%20rice%20may%20make%20no%20difference%20to%20anaemia%20levels.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%20reiterates%20the%20findings%20of%20a%20systematic%20review%20of%20research%20in%20health%20policy%2C%20used%20as%20a%20gold%20standard%20by%20research%20scholars%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20review%20(Cochrane%20system%20review)%20showed%20that%20the%20provision%20of%20rice%20fortified%20with%20vitamins%20and%20minerals%20including%20iron%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20probably%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20improves%20iron%20status%20by%20reducing%20risk%20of%20iron%20deficiency%20by%2035%25%20and%20increasing%20the%20average%20concentration%20of%20haemoglobin%20by%20almost%202g%2FL%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebut%20may%20not%20make%20a%20difference%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20anaemia%20in%20the%20general%20population%20of%20those%20aged%20over%202%20years%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162314%2F21-WHO-caveat-it-may-not-help-reduce-anemia.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22629%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162314%2F21-WHO-caveat-it-may-not-help-reduce-anemia.png%20629w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24162314%2F21-WHO-caveat-it-may-not-help-reduce-anemia-300x43.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686246%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%2291%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWHO%E2%80%99s%20guideline%20says%20iron-fortification%20may%20not%20make%20a%20difference%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20anaemia%20in%20most%20of%20the%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20recommended%20rice%20fortification%20with%20moderate%20evidence%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20requires%20continuous%20monitoring%2C%20and%20effective%20quality%20control%20systems.%20It%20says%20such%20a%20policy%20especially%20needs%20particular%20care%20through%20public%20health%20measures%20if%20fortified%20rice%20is%20distributed%20in%20malaria-endemic%20regions%2C%20which%20several%20parts%20of%20Jharkhand%2C%20Odisha%20in%20eastern%20India%20are.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20same%20WHO%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fbooks%2FNBK531767%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eguideline%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20thanks%20Bill%20and%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation%20along%20with%20the%20United%20States%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Efor%20%E2%80%9Cfinancial%20support%20for%20the%20guidelines%20development%20process%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20thanks%20GAIN%20for%20%E2%80%9Cpartial%20financial%20support%E2%80%9D%20for%20a%20prior%20meeting%20on%20technical%20aspects%20of%20fortification%20in%20Geneva%20on%208-9%20October%2C%202012%E2%80%9D%20with%20a%20disclaimer%20that%20donors%20do%20not%20fund%20specific%20guidelines.%20(Gates%20Foundation%20is%20the%20largest%20non-state%20funder%20of%20the%20WHO%20and%2C%20in%202021%20it%20was%20the%20second%20largest%20donor%20overall.%20Its%20growing%20influence%20over%20the%20WHO%20was%20also%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fqz.com%2F2102889%2Fthe-who-is-too-dependent-on-gates-foundation-donations%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecritiqued%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20that%20the%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%20grants%20are%20earmarked%20contributions%20and%20influence%2C%20de%20facto%2C%20the%20priority%20setting%20of%20the%20WHO.)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKuruganti%2C%20the%20agriculture%20activist%20pointed%20out%20the%20health%20infrastructure%20prerequisites%20such%20as%20outlined%20by%20WHO%20should%20have%20raised%20an%20alarm%20that%20the%20scheme%20does%20not%20fit%20in%20neatly%20in%20the%20Indian%20context%20at%20all.%20%E2%80%9COur%20safety%20debates%20are%20different%20from%20the%20other%20regions%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20home%20to%20many%20indigenous%20Adivasi%20communities%2C%20which%20have%20a%20substantial%20burden%20of%20diseases%20like%20malaria%2C%20tuberculosis%2C%20whom%20this%20rice%20may%20not%20be%20suitable%20for.%20Yet%2C%20fortification%20has%20been%20mandatory%20in%20to%20essential%20schemes%20such%20as%20food%20rations%2C%20children%E2%80%99s%20meals.%20Our%20socio-economic%20and%20cultural%20context%20is%20such%20that%20they%20do%20not%20allow%20these%20communities%20to%20make%20informed%20or%20conscious%20choices%2C%20they%20then%20have%20no%20alternatives%20to%20eating%20such%20fortified%20food%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kuruganti.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20complete%20influence%20of%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20and%20related%20entities%20is%20also%20evident%20in%20the%20government%20guidelines%20on%20rice%20fortification.%20These%20reproduced%20text%20verbatim%20from%20a%20PATH%20document.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20manual%E2%80%99s%20page%2089-90%20state%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20person%20who%20is%20suffering%20from%20any%20contagious%20or%20infectious%20disease%20is%20permitted%20to%20enter%20the%20packing%20area%20or%20touch%20Ultra%20Rice.%E2%80%9D%20or%20ensure%20%E2%80%9Cno%20chance%20of%20foreign%20objects%20falling%20into%20Ultra%20Rice.%E2%80%9D%20Ultra%20Rice%20is%20a%20technique%20invented%20by%20the%20Cox%20family%2C%20an%20American%20business%2C%20who%20gifted%20the%20technology%20patent%20to%20PATH%20in%201996-7%20which%20it%20uses%20to%20fortify%20rice.%20As%20per%20PATH%20website%2C%20the%20technology%20is%20disseminated%20in%20poor%20countries%20with%20a%20US%20%24%20six%20million%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.path.org%2Fmedia-center%2Fnew-funding-to-further-paths-rice-fortification-method%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egrant%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Efrom%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20along%20with%20USD%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abbott.com%2Fcorpnewsroom%2Fsustainability%2Fultra-rice.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E1.5%20million%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20the%20Abbott%20Fund%2C%20the%20philanthropy%20arm%20of%20the%20American%20nutrition%20corporation.%20These%20excerpts%20in%20draft%20guidelines%20that%20showing%20the%20copying%20of%20the%20PATH%20documents%20were%20corrected%20when%20the%20guidelines%20were%20published%20in%202019.%20The%20term%20%E2%80%9CUltra%20Rice%E2%80%9D%20was%20simply%20changed%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfortified%20rice.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FMkz8JRVBltA%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%26quot%3BPlastic%20Rice%26quot%3B%3A%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Experiment%20With%20Fortified%20Rice%20Hard%20to%20Swallow%20for%20India's%20Adivasi%20Residents%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EShrinking%20budgets%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Right%20to%20Food%20Campaign%20activists%20have%20since%20years%20opposed%20use%20of%20industrial%20products%20such%20as%20ready-to-use%20therapeutic%20food(RUTF)%2C%20fortificants%20in%20public%20schemes.%20They%20instead%20advocate%20for%20providing%20giving%20local%20fruits%2C%20vegetables%2C%20eggs%2C%20pulses%2C%20millets.%20But%2C%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20years%2C%20funds%20for%20social%20schemes%20which%20provide%20fresh%20cooked%20food%20to%20children%2C%20infants%2C%20women%20have%20been%20drastically%20cut.%20Development%20economists%20Jean%20Dreze%20and%20Reetika%20Khera%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fchart-decline-expenditure-social-security-schemes-budget-2023%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecalculated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20budget%20for%20school%20mid-day%20meals%2C%20or%20the%20PM-POSHAN%20scheme%2C%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiaspend.com%2Findiaspend-interviews%2Fno-point-in-india-growing-so-fast-if-wages-stagnate-and-social-spending-is-slashed-852240%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E43%25%20less%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20real%20terms%20than%20the%202014-15%20budget.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20budget%20for%20Integrated%20Child%20Development%20Services%20(ICDS)%20scheme%2C%20which%20serves%20freshly%20cooked%20meals%20at%20anganwadis%20or%20creches%20to%20infants%2C%20pregnant%20women%2C%20lactating%20mothers%20is%2040%20percent%20less%20in%20real%20terms%20than%20the%202014-15%20budget.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EProfessor%20Reetika%20Khera%20pointed%20out%20that%20of%20the%20ICSD%20budget%2C%20Rs%209000%20crore%20was%20spent%20on%20software%2C%20equivalent%20to%20money%20that%20would%20buy%20150%20eggs%20a%20year%20for%2010%20crore%20children%20enrolled%20in%20the%20scheme.%20Commenting%20on%20the%20growing%2C%20opaque%20influence%20of%20entities%20such%20as%20the%20BMGF%20and%20its%20related%20entities%20like%20PATH%2C%20she%20pointed%20out%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cprindia.org%2Fsystem%2Ftdf%2Fpolicy-briefs%2FPA-NMM-2020-21.pdf%3Ffile%3D1%26type%3Dnode%26id%3D8428%26force%3D1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMore%20than%2070%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20Poshan%20abhiyan%20budget%20was%20spent%20on%20community%20events%20and%20%E2%80%9Creal%20time%20monitoring%E2%80%9D%20through%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fkarnataka%2Fstate-to-start-icds-common-application-software-from-december%2Farticle29802377.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EICDS-CAS%20software%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20developed%20in%20collaboration%20with%20BMGF.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20expressed%20wariness%20over%20this%20turn%20to%20Gates%20Foundation-led%20prescriptions%20for%20nutrition.%20%E2%80%9CEarlier%2C%20we%20were%20concerned%20about%20shrinking%20budgets%20for%20social%20schemes%3B%20now%20increasingly%2C%20we%20worry%20about%20conflict%20of%20interest%20in%20policies%2C%20%E2%80%9Cfriendly%E2%80%9D%20research%2C%20a%20revolving%20door%2C%20institutional%20capture%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CConflict%20of%20interest%20is%20now%20characterized%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cwin-win%E2%80%9D%20proposition%20(%E2%80%9Cwhat%E2%80%99s%20the%20harm%20if%20the%20private%20sector%20profits%20off%20reducing%20malnutrition%E2%80%9D)%3F%20This%20undermines%20multi-lateral%20agencies%20and%20governments%20%E2%80%93%20how%20can%20they%20can%20function%20democratically%20when%20they%20rely%20heavily%20on%20funds%20from%20these%20few%20sources%3F%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20questioned%20why%20instead%2C%20local%20political%20representatives%20from%20among%20the%20affected%20vulnerable%20communities%20were%20hardly%20invited%20to%20policy%20consultations%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20are%20there%20no%20village%20sarpanch%2C%20or%20even%20ordinary%20farm%20workers%20who%20are%20affected%20on%20such%20government%20committees%3F%20Why%20only%20these%20%E2%80%9Cconsultants%E2%80%9D%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20asked.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20part%20one%C2%A0%3Ca%20h