ople%20to%20stand%20up%20and%20be%20counted.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20go%20down%20to%20the%20wire%2C%20on%20what%20each%20of%20the%20numbers%20unveiled%20mean.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWho%20are%20the%20people%20referred%20to%20by%20percentages%20in%20the%20survey%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EToday%20we%20look%20at%20Dhuniya%20(18%2C68%2C192%20people)%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20of%20a%20Dhuniya%20is%20to%20scutch%20cotton.%20In%20rural%20areas%2C%20people%20of%20this%20caste%20can%20be%20seen%20carrying%20%3Cem%3Edhanuhi%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Ejista%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20their%20shoulders%20even%20today.%20%3Cem%3ETant%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20%3Cem%3Edhanuhi%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20strong%20rope%20which%20is%20made%20by%20drying%20the%20intestines%20of%20dead%20animals.%20They%20hit%20the%20%3Cem%3Edhanuhi%3C%2Fem%3E%20with%20the%20%3Cem%3Ejista%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20beat%20cotton.%20It%20has%20been%20a%20traditional%20and%20noble%20profession.%20The%20cotton%20fluffed%20up%20by%20them%20is%20used%20in%20several%20ways%2C%20such%20as%20making%20thread%20which%20in%20turn%20is%20used%20to%20make%20clothes.%20Cotton%20is%20also%20used%20in%20towels%2C%20quilts%20and%20pillows%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20375px)%2085vw%2C%20375px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22375%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%20838w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-210x300.jpg%20210w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%20715w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682410%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22537%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDhuniyas%20are%20Muslims%20who%20fall%20in%20the%20backward%20category.%20One%20may%20call%20them%20Pasmanda%2C%20which%20means%20people%20left%20behind%2C%20as%20against%20the%20Ashraf.%20Interestingly%2C%20Tipu%20Sultan%20belonged%20to%20this%20caste%2C%20whose%20indomitable%20courage%20is%20inscribed%20in%20gilded%20letters%20in%20the%20history%20of%20India.%20Those%20who%20frown%20at%20the%20name%20of%20Tipu%20Sultan%20know%20that%20the%20blood%20of%20Pinjara%20or%20Dhuniya%20of%20Shramana%20tradition%20flowed%20through%20his%20veins.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20Dhuniyas%20among%20Hindus%20but%20they%20had%20learned%20this%20art%20from%20Muslim%20Dhuniyas.%20As%20far%20as%20their%20place%20of%20origin%20is%20concerned%2C%20they%20do%20not%20hail%20from%20here%20but%20are%20basically%20natives%20of%20Persia%20(today%E2%80%99s%20Iran)%20and%20Afghanistan.%20But%20now%20many%20of%20their%20generations%20are%20buried%20in%20graves%20in%20this%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20they%20were%20called%20Pinjara%20and%20not%20Dhuniya%2C%20but%20their%20job%20was%20the%20same%20as%20it%20is%20today.%20In%20India%2C%20three%20terms%20are%20used%20to%20refer%20to%20them%20%E2%80%93%20Pinjara%2C%20Mansoori%20and%20Dhuniya.%20In%20Gujarat%2C%20they%20are%20called%20Mansoori.%20However%2C%20Bihar%20also%20has%20a%20sizeable%20population%20of%20Mansooris%2C%20including%20in%20Gaya%20and%20Bhagalpur%20and%20its%20surrounding%20districts.%20They%20also%20have%20a%20significant%20population%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20eastern%20belt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20classical%20mystic%20poet%20Kabir%20was%20a%20weaver%2C%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Dhuniya%20community%20considered%20Kabir%20as%20their%20guru.%20Radha%20Swami%20sect%20is%20a%20sect%20inspired%20by%20Kabir.%20Dhuniya%20people%20also%20believed%20in%20this%20sect%2C%20which%20is%20highlighted%20in%20several%20hymns%20written%20by%20Shiv%20Dayal%20Singh%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20Radha%20Swami%20sect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDhuniyas%20have%20been%20closely%20associated%20with%20religion.%20One%20example%20is%20Persian%20Sufi%20mystic%20Mansur%20al-Hallaj%20who%20was%20also%20a%20weaver%20like%20Kabir.%20His%20followers%20were%20called%20Mansoori.%20It%20is%20documented%20in%20history%20that%20they%20first%20landed%20in%20Gujarat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20other%20stories%20are%20being%20spread%20these%20days%20by%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20that%20the%20Pinjara%20caste%20originated%20in%20India%20and%20they%20were%20originally%20Hindus%20from%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20all%20such%20claims%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20they%20are%20a%20backward%20Muslim%20community%20and%20face%20neglect%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20their%20population%20in%20Bihar%20is%2018%2C68%2C192.%20Most%20political%20parties%20have%20also%20ignored%20this%20caste%20till%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20of%20this%20caste%20travelled%20far%20to%20reach%20India%20from%20Iran%20and%20made%20this%20country%20their%20home.%20Now%2C%20India%20is%20their%20country%20and%20they%20are%20its%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F261388%2Fbihar-caste-survey-dhunia-caste-society-politics%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20earlier%20parts%20of%20the%20series%20on%20the%20following%20communities%20by%20clicking%20on%20their%20names%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-ghasi%5C%22%3EGhasi%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3ESantrash%3C