C%20warranting%20the%20reconsideration%20of%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20expression%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20possible%E2%80%9D%20is%20significant.%20It%20conveys%20a%20constitutional%20imperative%20of%20expedition.%20Failure%20to%20take%20a%20call%20and%20keeping%20a%20Bill%20duly%20passed%20for%20indeterminate%20periods%20is%20a%20course%20of%20action%20inconsistent%20with%20that%20expression.%20Constitutional%20language%20is%20not%20surplusage%2C%E2%80%9D%20its%20judgment%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20said%20that%20failing%20to%20read%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20power%20in%20Article%20200%20in%20this%20manner%20would%20put%20him%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cposition%20to%20virtually%20veto%E2%80%9D%20the%20elected%20legislature%E2%80%99s%20functioning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20a%20course%20of%20action%20would%20be%20contrary%20to%20%5Bthe%5D%20fundamental%20principles%20of%20a%20constitutional%20democracy%20based%20on%20a%20parliamentary%20pattern%20of%20governance%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20governors%20are%20required%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdeclare%E2%80%9D%20which%20option%20they%20choose%20to%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20remarks%20were%20made%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20three-judge%20bench%2C%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fsc-talks-tough-on-punjab-tn-governors-sitting-over-bills-says-dont-play-with-fire%2F1840999%2F%5C%22%3ENovember%2010%20ruling%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20based%20on%20a%20plea%20by%20the%20Punjab%20government%20against%20governor%20Banwarilal%20Purohit.%20The%20governor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgovernors-inaction-bills-supreme-court-punjab%5C%22%3Ehad%20kept%3C%2Fa%3E%20seven%20Bills%2C%20sent%20to%20him%20by%20the%20state%20legislature%2C%20pending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%E2%80%99s%20detailed%20judgment%20was%20made%20public%20on%20Thursday%2C%20November%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgovernors-as-ruling-partys-storm-troopers%5C%22%3EGovernors%20as%20Ruling%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Storm%20Troopers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImplications%20for%20other%20states%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkerala-moves-sc-governor-arif-mohammad-khan-bills-hold-indefinitely%5C%22%3ESimilar%20petitions%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20filed%20by%20the%20Kerala%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam-led%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20had%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20October%20over%20governor%20R.N.%20Ravi%E2%80%99s%20delay%20in%20clearing%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20state%20legislature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20Bills%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Frn-ravi-tn-govt-row-sc-says-law-does-not-give-governor-discretion-to-withhold-bills-re-passed-by-assembly%2Farticle67553775.ece%5C%22%3E%20had%20been%20sent%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20approval%20to%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20office%20in%20the%20period%20between%20January%202020%20to%20April%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20plea%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20on%20November%2010%2C%20said%20that%20this%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmatter%20of%20serious%20concern%E2%80%9D%20and%20issued%20a%20notice%20to%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Ftn-governors-delay-in-dealing-with-bills-an-issue-of-serious-concern-says-sc%2Farticle67520494.ece%5C%22%3EPTI%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20days%20later%2C%20Ravi%20returned%2010%20Bills%20to%20the%20legislature%20for%20reconsideration%2C%20following%20which%