%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fmob-storms-imphal-hospital-treating-man-injured-myanmar-fighting-9040206%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%20the%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fmob-storms-imphal-hospital-treating-man-injured-myanmar-fighting-9040206%2F%5C%22%3E%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPolice%20said%20the%20man%2C%20identified%20as%20Khoantum%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Thanan%2C%20in%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20Sagaing%20region%2C%20died%20at%20the%20hospital%20on%20Thursday%20afternoon%20of%20bullet%20injuries%20that%20he%20suffered%20during%20the%20fighting%20in%20Myanmar%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20news%20report%20said.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20mob%20had%20gathered%20at%20JNIMS%20due%20to%20a%20rumour%20that%20the%20man%20was%20a%20militant%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Myanmarese%20man%20was%20given%20first%20aid%20by%20the%20Assam%20Rifles%20that%20man%20the%20border%2C%20before%20being%20handedm%20over%20to%20the%20state%20police%20at%20around%203.55%20am%20on%20November%2023.%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20that%2C%20they%20would%20have%20taken%20him%20to%20Imphal%20for%20further%20treatment%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20security%20official%20told%20%3Cem%3EIndian%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EExpress%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20succumbed%20to%20his%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWithin%20Manipur%2C%20the%20Community%20on%20Tribal%20Unity%20(CoTU)%20belonging%20to%20the%20Kuki%20community%20has%20reimposed%20the%20blockade%20of%20the%20National%20Highways%202%20and%2037%20that%20pass%20by%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20Kangpokpi%20district%2C%20located%20about%2045%20kms%20from%20Imphal.%20CoTU%20has%20accused%20the%20government%20of%20not%20ensuring%20law%20and%20order%20in%20the%20Kuki-dominated%20areas.%20The%20blockade%20of%20these%20highways%20typically%20chokes%20the%20supply%20of%20essentials%20to%20the%20valley%20areas%2C%20the%20home%20to%20the%20Meitei%20community%2C%20which%20swells%20the%20animosity%20between%20the%20two%20clashing%20communities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700810320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24124703%2FScreenshot-2023-11-24-at-12.46.3.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fmanipur-myanmar-meitei-kuki-chin%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20in%20the%20Imphal%20Free%20Press%20also%20said%20that%20on%20the%20same%20day%2C%20another%20valley-based%20(Meitei)%20underground%20outfit%20%E2%80%9Creportedly%20exchanged%20a%20gunfight%20with%20PDF%20at%20Thanan%20in%20Myanmar%20around%20noon.%E2%80%9D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fmanipur-myanmar-meitei-kuki-chin%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reconsidering%20PMLA%20Judgment%3A%20Justice%20Kaul-Led%20Bench%20Abandons%20Hearing%20As%20Centre%20Seeks%20More%20Time%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2F09153755%2Fsanjay-kaul.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20a%20sense%2C%20the%20hearing%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Special%20Bench%2C%20which%20agreed%20to%20revisit%20its%202022%20judgment%20upholding%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA)%20was%20doomed%20from%20the%20start%2C%20with%20the%20Union%20government%20questioning%20its%20legitimacy.%20Yet%2C%20Justice%20S.K.%20Kaul%2C%20who%20led%20the%20three-judge%20bench%20also%20comprising%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20Bela%20M.%20Trivedi%2C%20sought%20to%20go%20ahead%20with%20the%20hearing%20initially%2C%20dismissing%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20contentions%20against%20the%20bench%E2%80%99s%20jurisdiction%20to%20hear%20the%20case%20with%20the%20hope%20that%20it%20would%20be%20able%20to%20complete%20the%20hearing%20and%20deliver%20a%20verdict%20before%20Justice%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%20last%20day%20in%20office%20on%20December%2016%2C%20prelude%20to%20his%20retirement%20on%20December%2025.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%2023%2C%20Thursday%2C%20the%20second%20day%20of%20the%20hearing%2C%20however%2C%20the%20bench%20understood%20the%20futility%20of%20hearing%20the%20case%2C%20with%20the%20Union%20government%20continuing%20to%20obstruct%20the%20hearing.%20Solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%2C%20who%20realised%20that%20he%20could%20not%20persuade%20the%20bench%20not%20to%20hear%20the%20case%2C%20sought%20more%20time%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20arguments%20of%20the%20petitioners%2C%20who%20he%20alleged%2C%20had%20%E2%80%9Cexpanded%20their%20challenge%20to%20the%202022%20verdict%20beyond%20the%20issues%20they%20had%20initially%20raised%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Wednesday%20and%20Thursday%2C%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20senior%20counsel%2C%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20made%20detailed%20submissions%20before%20the%20bench%2C%20which%20in%20retrospect%2C%20seemed%20to%20be%20in%20vain.%20Senior%20counsel%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%2C%20who%20made%20submissions%20on%20behalf%20of%20another%20petitioner%20Sanjay%20Chabbaria%20on%20Thursday%2C%20vehemently%20protested%20against%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20plea%20for%20more%20time%20to%20respond%2C%20saying%20the%20petitioners%20had%20not%20raised%20any%20new%20points%2C%20and%20were%20not%20pressing%20their%20amendments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENotwithstanding%20the%20waste%20of%20judicial%20time%2C%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20plea%20landed%20the%20bench%20in%20a%20quandary.%20Justice%20Kaul%20pleaded%20helplessness%2C%20by%20saying%20he%20was%20adjourning%20the%20hearing%2C%20and%20placing%20the%20case%20before%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20for%20constituting%20a%20new%20bench%20to%20hear%20it%2C%20in%20view%20of%20his%20impending%20retirement.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20doing%20this%20with%20a%20little%20heavy%20heart%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20while%20dictating%20the%20order.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20response%20to%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20plea%20for%20more%20time%20to%20respond%20to%20new%20points%20in%20the%20amended%20petition%2C%20Justice%20Kaul%20said%20tongue-in-cheek%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20everything.%20But%20sometimes%2C%20things%20must%20be%20left%20unsaid.%E2%80%9D%20He%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9COn%20this%20side%2C%20we%20see%20and%20hear%20many%20things%2C%20but%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20say%20many%20things.%20On%20a%20lighter%20note%2C%20I%20will%20have%20that%20privilege%20from%20January%201.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackground%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20case%20before%20the%20special%20bench%20sought%20a%20reference%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20previous%20decision%20in%20%3Cem%3EVijay%20Madanlal%20Choudhary%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022)%20to%20a%20larger%20bench.%20The%202022%20judgment%20was%20rendered%20by%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20A.M.%20Khanwilkar%2C%20Dinesh%20Maheshwari%20and%20C.T.%20Ravi%20Kumar.%20The%20judgment%2C%20authored%20by%20Justice%20Khanwilkar%20two%20days%20before%20his%20retirement%2C%20upheld%20the%20wide%20powers%20of%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Enforcement%20(ED)%20to%20issue%20summons%2C%20record%20statements%2C%20make%20arrests%20and%20search%20and%20seize%20property.%20It%20was%20also%20held%20that%20the%20Act%2C%20which%20imposes%20its%20own%20bail%20conditions%2C%20is%20not%20a%20penal%20law.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMehta%20opposed%20the%20hearing%20by%20the%20special%20bench%20%E2%80%93%20also%20comprising%20three%20judges%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20reconsideration%20of%20a%20coordinate%20bench%20decision%20was%20an%20%E2%80%98abuse%20of%20the%20process%20of%20law%E2%80%99.%20Mehta%20also%20opposed%20it%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20a%20review%20petition%20against%20the%202022%20judgment%20was%20pending%20before%20the%20court.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Justice%20Kaul-led%20bench%2C%20however%2C%20rejected%20the%20contention%20by%20relying%20on%20precedents%20to%20justify%20the%20reconsideration%20of%20a%20judgment%20by%20a%20coordinate%20bench%20of%20similar%20strength.%C2%A0%20The%20bench%20reserved%20its%20right%20to%20consider%20whether%20the%20case%20should%20be%20referred%20to%20a%20larger%20bench.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20Sibal%20contended%20before%20the%20bench%20that%20the%202022%20judgment%20erroneously%20upheld%20provisions%20which%20breached%20personal%20liberty%20under%20Article%2021.%20On%20Thursday%2C%20Singhvi%20sought%20to%20substantiate%20that%20amendments%20to%20Section%2045%20of%20the%20PMLA%20%E2%80%93%20relating%20to%20cognisable%20and%20non-bailable%20offences%20%E2%80%93%20were%20wrongfully%20upheld%20in%20the%202022%20judgment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20composition%20of%20the%20new%20bench%2C%20to%20be%20constituted%20by%20the%20CJI%2C%20to%20hear%20the%20case%2C%20will%20indicate%20whether%20the%20case%20will%20at%20all%20be%20heard%20by%20a%20larger%20bench.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700809201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2F09153755%2Fsanjay-kaul.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Freconsidering-pmla-judgment-justice-kaul-abandon-hearing-centre-more-time%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20sought%20more%20time%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20arguments%2C%20Justice%20S.K.%20Kaul%2C%20who%20will%20retire%20on%20December%2025%2C%20had%20no%20option%20but%20to%20discontinue%20further%20hearing.%22%2